WEBVTT

1
00:00:22.343 --> 00:00:23.431
Radio: MARINERS BE ADVISED,
[THUNDER]


2
00:00:23.474 --> 00:00:24.693
A VIOLENT STORM
IS CONVERGING


3
00:00:24.736 --> 00:00:26.869
ON THE NORTHERN
AND CENTRAL CALIFORNIA COAST


4
00:00:26.912 --> 00:00:28.523
WITH WINDS
UP TO HURRICANE FORCE.


5
00:00:30.133 --> 00:00:31.526
Man: COAST GUARD BASE
MONTEREY,


6
00:00:31.569 --> 00:00:33.745
COME IN. COME IN.

7
00:00:38.402 --> 00:00:40.274
THERE'S NO POWER!

8
00:00:40.317 --> 00:00:42.102
THE PUMPS DON'T WORK!

9
00:00:42.145 --> 00:00:43.451
MAYDAY! MAYDAY!

10
00:00:43.494 --> 00:00:45.801
WE'RE SINKING! MAYDAY!

11
00:00:51.589 --> 00:00:53.504
RICK!

12
00:00:53.548 --> 00:00:54.549
RICK!

13
00:00:54.592 --> 00:00:56.377
JASON!

14
00:00:56.420 --> 00:00:58.118
Susan: WHEN YOU'RE
FIGHTING FOR YOUR LIFE,


15
00:00:58.161 --> 00:01:00.990
YOU'VE GOT TO HAVE A REASON
TO KEEP GOING.


16
00:01:01.033 --> 00:01:04.559
YOU'VE GOT TO LOVE SOMEONE
OR SOMETHING SO MUCH


17
00:01:04.602 --> 00:01:06.735
THAT YOU REFUSE TO GIVE UP.

18
00:01:06.778 --> 00:01:08.128
I FOUND MY REASON
AFTER OUR BOAT SANK


19
00:01:08.171 --> 00:01:10.260
TO THE BOTTOM
OF THE PACIFIC OCEAN.


20
00:01:11.174 --> 00:01:15.091
♪ JUMP, HEY, GIRL

21
00:01:15.135 --> 00:01:16.919
♪ COME ON

22
00:01:16.962 --> 00:01:18.703
♪ COME ON AROUND HERE

23
00:01:18.747 --> 00:01:19.704
♪ THAT'S BETTER

24
00:01:19.748 --> 00:01:20.923
♪ WHAT YOU WANT, GIRL?

25
00:01:20.966 --> 00:01:22.968
♪ THERE'S A PARTY OVER HERE

26
00:01:23.012 --> 00:01:24.361
♪ UH
-HUH, YEAH

27
00:01:24.405 --> 00:01:26.450
Man: LOOK OUT.
SHE'S ON FIRE TODAY.


28
00:01:26.494 --> 00:01:29.627
♪ AND I SAY, YEAH

29
00:01:29.671 --> 00:01:31.977
♪ SEEMS LIKE OLD TIMES

30
00:01:32.021 --> 00:01:33.979
OOH
-WHOO! YEAH!

31
00:01:34.023 --> 00:01:37.940
TIP OF THE DAY.
LOSER BUYS, ALL RIGHT?


32
00:01:37.983 --> 00:01:41.378
♪ JUST WAVE GOOD
-BYE

33
00:01:41.422 --> 00:01:46.557
♪ THESE ARE THE TIMES,
THE TIMES OF OUR LIVES ♪


34
00:01:46.601 --> 00:01:49.473
♪ THESE ARE THE DAYS

35
00:01:49.517 --> 00:01:52.824
♪ THESE ARE THE DAYS,
THESE ARE THE DAYS ♪


36
00:01:52.868 --> 00:01:55.044
♪ OF OUR LIVES

37
00:01:55.087 --> 00:01:57.525
♪ THESE ARE THE NIGHTS

38
00:01:57.568 --> 00:01:59.657
♪ THESE ARE THE NIGHTS

39
00:01:59.701 --> 00:02:04.096
♪ KEEP ON GOING

40
00:02:04.140 --> 00:02:07.012
♪ WHOO! COME ON, NOW

41
00:02:07.056 --> 00:02:10.102
♪ YEAH, ALL RIGHT

42
00:02:10.146 --> 00:02:11.321
♪ HEY

43
00:02:18.285 --> 00:02:19.938
♪ I WON'T BE HASTY...

44
00:02:19.982 --> 00:02:21.288
LET'S SEE, WHAT WOULD
I LIKE TO DRINK?


45
00:02:21.331 --> 00:02:22.898
I CAN HAVE
ANYTHING I WANT, RIGHT?


46
00:02:22.941 --> 00:02:24.813
NOBODY LIKES
A SMUG WINNER.


47
00:02:24.856 --> 00:02:27.685
DEBBIE, GIVE HIM
THE CHEAPEST THING ON TAP.
NOTHING FOR ME.


48
00:02:27.729 --> 00:02:30.645
SO TELL ME ABOUT
THIS PROPOSAL OF YOURS.


49
00:02:30.688 --> 00:02:33.082
OK.

50
00:02:33.125 --> 00:02:34.431
HOW WOULD YOU LIKE
TO MAKE GOOD MONEY


51
00:02:34.475 --> 00:02:36.999
ON A BEAUTIFUL BOAT
WITH A KILLER CREW?


52
00:02:37.042 --> 00:02:38.827
THIS GUY I SAILED WITH
LAST YEAR, RICK FOSTER,


53
00:02:38.870 --> 00:02:41.612
HE'S BRINGING A 68-FOOT IRWIN
UP TO VANCOUVER NEXT WEEK, OK?


54
00:02:41.656 --> 00:02:43.919
IT'S A PRIVATE GIG.
HE'S DELIVERING IT
TO THE OWNER.


55
00:02:43.962 --> 00:02:44.920
WE NEED A CREW. WE...

56
00:02:44.963 --> 00:02:45.877
MATT, I DON'T KNOW.

57
00:02:45.921 --> 00:02:47.357
COME ON.
IT'D BE A BLAST.


58
00:02:47.401 --> 00:02:49.403
IT SOUNDS GREAT.
I'M SURE WE'D HAVE FUN.


59
00:02:49.446 --> 00:02:51.840
BUT YOU KNOW I'VE
GIVEN UP SAILING
FOR A WHILE.


60
00:02:51.883 --> 00:02:53.929
NOW, THAT'S THE MOST
TRAGIC THING
I'VE HEARD ALL DAY.


61
00:02:53.972 --> 00:02:54.669
HEY, HEY, HEY.

62
00:02:54.712 --> 00:02:56.192
RICK FOSTER.

63
00:02:56.236 --> 00:02:57.411
PLEASURE
TO MEET YOU,
MS. CLARKSON.


64
00:02:57.454 --> 00:02:59.195
NICE TO MEET YOU.

65
00:02:59.239 --> 00:03:00.805
YOU SNEAK. YOU PLANNED THIS,
DIDN'T YOU?


66
00:03:00.849 --> 00:03:02.024
GUILTY AS CHARGED.

67
00:03:02.067 --> 00:03:03.286
PLAN WAS
TO AMBUSH YOU.


68
00:03:03.330 --> 00:03:05.854
NOW, TELL ME WHY
YOU'RE LANDLOCKED.


69
00:03:05.897 --> 00:03:07.290
BUNCH OF REASONS.

70
00:03:07.334 --> 00:03:08.987
I GOTTA SETTLE DOWN,
FIND A STEADY JOB.


71
00:03:09.031 --> 00:03:10.206
I UNDERSTAND.

72
00:03:10.250 --> 00:03:12.295
IT'LL ONLY BE
A COUPLE OF WEEKS.


73
00:03:12.339 --> 00:03:13.470
OWNER WANTS
THE BOAT
IN VANCOUVER


74
00:03:13.514 --> 00:03:14.863
BY THE END
OF THE MONTH.


75
00:03:14.906 --> 00:03:17.039
I'LL PAY 500
PLUS EXPENSES.


76
00:03:17.082 --> 00:03:18.345
THAT SOUNDS GREAT.

77
00:03:18.388 --> 00:03:19.302
EXCELLENT.

78
00:03:19.346 --> 00:03:21.173
WE SET SAIL
NEXT WEEK.


79
00:03:21.217 --> 00:03:22.697
BUT I CAN'T.

80
00:03:22.740 --> 00:03:25.395
THANKS FOR THE OFFER.
I REALLY WISH I COULD.


81
00:03:25.439 --> 00:03:28.006
IT WAS NICE
TO MEET YOU, RICK.


82
00:03:28.050 --> 00:03:28.790
SEE YOU LATER, MATT.

83
00:03:28.833 --> 00:03:29.965
RIGHT.

84
00:03:32.010 --> 00:03:33.490
I'LL CALL YOU.

85
00:03:33.534 --> 00:03:37.015
DON'T WORRY.
WE GOT OTHER PEOPLE
WE CAN GO TO.


86
00:03:37.059 --> 00:03:38.669
NOT LIKE HER.

87
00:03:38.713 --> 00:03:41.846
SO, MATT, HOW MUCH
OF THIS INTEREST
IS PROFESSIONAL?


88
00:03:41.890 --> 00:03:42.978
ALL OF IT.

89
00:03:47.243 --> 00:03:48.810
ALL RIGHT.
WELL, MOST OF IT.


90
00:03:48.853 --> 00:03:50.551
ANY LUCK YESTERDAY?

91
00:03:50.594 --> 00:03:52.117
NOTHING I COULD HANDLE.

92
00:03:52.161 --> 00:03:56.513
$6.00 AN HOUR TO GIVE
BOAT RIDES TO TOURISTS
JUST ISN'T ME.


93
00:03:56.557 --> 00:03:59.255
MAYBE SOMETHING
WITHOUT BOATS WOULD
BE NICE FOR A CHANGE.


94
00:03:59.299 --> 00:04:01.083
MAYBE.

95
00:04:03.128 --> 00:04:04.521
SUSANNAH, I, UM...

96
00:04:04.565 --> 00:04:05.522
UH
-OH.

97
00:04:05.566 --> 00:04:07.568
UH
-OH WHAT?

98
00:04:07.611 --> 00:04:09.178
THAT'S WHAT YOU USED TO
CALL ME WHEN I WAS A KID


99
00:04:09.221 --> 00:04:12.573
AND WE WERE GONNA
HAVE ONE OF OUR TALKS.


100
00:04:12.616 --> 00:04:15.358
BUT I CAN'T HELP NOT
WANTING YOU TO LEAVE
AGAIN, NOT YET,


101
00:04:15.402 --> 00:04:17.273
NOT WHEN I FEEL LIKE
WE'RE FINALLY STARTING
TO TALK.


102
00:04:17.317 --> 00:04:18.405
I'M NOT LEAVING.

103
00:04:18.448 --> 00:04:20.407
IN FACT, I JUST
TURNED DOWN AN OFFER


104
00:04:20.450 --> 00:04:22.365
TO SAIL A 68-FOOTER
UP THE COAST.


105
00:04:23.627 --> 00:04:26.326
I WORRY SO MUCH
WHEN YOU'RE OUT THERE.


106
00:04:26.369 --> 00:04:27.805
I JUST WISH YOUR FATHER
HADN'T MADE YOU...


107
00:04:27.849 --> 00:04:30.112
HE DIDN'T MAKE ME
LOVE THE OCEAN.


108
00:04:30.155 --> 00:04:31.983
I JUST ALWAYS HAVE.

109
00:04:32.027 --> 00:04:33.420
IT'S LIKE I NEVER
HAD A CHOICE.


110
00:04:35.204 --> 00:04:37.511
SUCH A NOMADIC
LIFESTYLE.


111
00:04:37.554 --> 00:04:40.340
CONSTANTLY MOVING,
CHANGING FRIENDS.


112
00:04:40.383 --> 00:04:42.080
I NEVER KNOW
WHERE YOU ARE,
WHETHER YOU'RE SAFE.


113
00:04:42.124 --> 00:04:42.951
MOM, STOP PUSHING.

114
00:05:06.235 --> 00:05:07.976
GUESS WHO.

115
00:05:08.019 --> 00:05:09.934
SOMEONE WHO WON'T
TAKE NO FOR AN ANSWER.


116
00:05:09.978 --> 00:05:11.980
COME ON. YOU'RE
GONNA TAKE THE REST
OF THE DAY OFF.


117
00:05:12.023 --> 00:05:13.808
IT'S 10:20. THE DAY
HASN'T EVEN STARTED.


118
00:05:13.851 --> 00:05:15.549
WELL, ALL THE MORE REASON
TO TAKE ADVANTAGE OF IT.


119
00:05:15.592 --> 00:05:17.594
NO, I CAN'T.
I HAVE TO FIND A JOB.


120
00:05:17.638 --> 00:05:18.552
COME ON.

121
00:05:18.595 --> 00:05:20.292
NO, REALLY,
I CAN'T. I CAN'T.


122
00:05:21.206 --> 00:05:22.469
SO WHY IS
YOUR MOTHER


123
00:05:22.512 --> 00:05:24.296
SO DEAD SET
AGAINST SAILING?


124
00:05:24.340 --> 00:05:25.602
MY DAD WAS A SAILOR.

125
00:05:25.646 --> 00:05:28.562
NOT SAILBOAT RACING.
YOU KNOW, SHIPYARD STUFF.


126
00:05:28.605 --> 00:05:30.520
HE LEFT
WHEN I WAS 10,


127
00:05:30.564 --> 00:05:32.870
TOOK A JOB
ON SOME OIL RIG,
AND THAT WAS THAT.


128
00:05:32.914 --> 00:05:35.307
WOW. I'M SORRY.

129
00:05:35.351 --> 00:05:38.354
IT'S OK.
IT WAS YEARS AGO.


130
00:05:38.398 --> 00:05:40.574
SO WHY ARE YOU
TAKING THIS GIG?


131
00:05:42.489 --> 00:05:45.274
ALL I WANT TO DO IS
BUILD MY RACING BOAT,


132
00:05:45.317 --> 00:05:47.363
AND THAT'S WHY
I'M TAKING THIS JOB
WITH RICK.


133
00:05:47.407 --> 00:05:50.018
THAT'S WHY I TAKE
ALL MY JOBS.


134
00:05:50.061 --> 00:05:51.019
WELL, GOOD LUCK.

135
00:05:51.062 --> 00:05:52.150
THANK YOU.

136
00:05:59.767 --> 00:06:00.942
WOW.

137
00:06:03.292 --> 00:06:05.599
Matt: SHE'S A BEAUTY, HUH?

138
00:06:05.642 --> 00:06:08.166
GO ON. GO FOR IT. RICK
WANTS TO SHOW YOU AROUND.


139
00:06:08.210 --> 00:06:09.516
KEEP AN OPEN MIND.

140
00:06:15.217 --> 00:06:17.785
NOT TOO SHABBY, HUH?

141
00:06:17.828 --> 00:06:18.742
IT'S AN IRWIN.

142
00:06:18.786 --> 00:06:21.528
BEAUTIFUL
CRAFTSMANSHIP.


143
00:06:21.571 --> 00:06:23.225
AND SHE'S
CERTAINLY GOT
ALL THE TOYS.


144
00:06:25.706 --> 00:06:27.838
SO, WHEN DID YOU DO
THE WHITBREAD?


145
00:06:27.882 --> 00:06:30.493
UM, HALFWAY THROUGH
MY SOPHOMORE YEAR
OF COLLEGE.


146
00:06:30.537 --> 00:06:31.799
AROUND THE WORLD.

147
00:06:31.842 --> 00:06:33.844
ALL THE WAY.

148
00:06:33.888 --> 00:06:36.325
WOW. HA.

149
00:06:36.368 --> 00:06:37.761
WELCOME TO "NO SWEAT"
SAILING.


150
00:06:37.805 --> 00:06:39.459
GO ON.
TAKE A LOOK AROUND.


151
00:06:49.947 --> 00:06:53.037
♪ IT'S GONNA TAKE A LOT
TO SATISFY ME... ♪


152
00:06:53.081 --> 00:06:54.561
UM, HELLO?

153
00:06:54.604 --> 00:06:55.953
HI.

154
00:06:55.997 --> 00:06:57.433
WHO ARE YOU?

155
00:06:57.477 --> 00:06:59.479
SUSAN CLARKSON.
I'M A FRIEND OF MATT'S.


156
00:06:59.522 --> 00:07:01.089
OH, RIGHT.

157
00:07:01.132 --> 00:07:04.875
YOU MUST BE THAT GIRL
THAT RICK'S BEEN
BABBLING ABOUT.


158
00:07:04.919 --> 00:07:06.921
YOU WON THE WHITE BREAD
OR SOMETHING.


159
00:07:06.964 --> 00:07:09.401
I'M ALLIE.

160
00:07:09.445 --> 00:07:11.273
SO ARE YOU ON THE CREW?

161
00:07:11.316 --> 00:07:15.669
NO. THE ONLY THING
I DO ON A BOAT IS TAN.


162
00:07:15.712 --> 00:07:16.974
RICK'S MY BOYFRIEND.

163
00:07:17.018 --> 00:07:19.586
I'M JUST ALONG
FOR THE RIDE.


164
00:07:19.629 --> 00:07:20.717
I THOUGHT I'D BE
THE ONLY WOMAN
ON BOARD, BUT...


165
00:07:20.761 --> 00:07:22.632
NO, I'M NOT GOING.

166
00:07:22.676 --> 00:07:25.287
OH, WELL.

167
00:07:25.330 --> 00:07:28.551
GUESS I'LL JUST HAVE
TO HANDLE THOSE BOYS
ON MY OWN.


168
00:07:28.595 --> 00:07:30.335
NICE TO MEET YOU, SUSAN.

169
00:07:30.379 --> 00:07:32.599
SEE YOU LATER.

170
00:07:35.732 --> 00:07:37.299
I'M TELLING YOU,
IT'LL BE FINE.


171
00:07:37.342 --> 00:07:39.562
AND I'M TELLING YOU,
WHY DO NOT HAVE ENOUGH TIME.


172
00:07:39.606 --> 00:07:40.389
WHAT, YOU WANNA BE
THE SKIPPER NOW,


173
00:07:40.432 --> 00:07:42.304
MAKE ALL
THE BIG DECISIONS?


174
00:07:42.347 --> 00:07:45.612
OF COURSE NOT, RICK.
I JUST THINK YOU'RE
PUSHING IT HERE, OK?


175
00:07:45.655 --> 00:07:48.136
AND I DON'T...
SUSAN. HEY.


176
00:07:48.179 --> 00:07:50.399
HEY. HOW'D IT GO?
WHAT'D YOU THINK?


177
00:07:50.442 --> 00:07:53.402
I JUST MET YOUR,
UM... ALLIE.


178
00:07:53.445 --> 00:07:54.577
OH, YEAH?

179
00:07:54.621 --> 00:07:56.405
SHE'S KIND OF
HIGH MAINTENANCE.


180
00:07:56.448 --> 00:07:57.537
AMAZING, THOUGH.

181
00:07:57.580 --> 00:07:58.929
KIND OF
HIGH MAINTENANCE?


182
00:08:00.496 --> 00:08:02.280
WHAT ARE YOU GUYS
TALKING ABOUT?


183
00:08:02.324 --> 00:08:05.109
NOTHING, JUST BUSINESS.

184
00:08:05.153 --> 00:08:06.676
SO, ANYWAY, SUSAN,

185
00:08:06.720 --> 00:08:08.852
I DON'T LIKE TO BEG,

186
00:08:08.896 --> 00:08:11.725
BUT WE COULD REALLY
USE YOU ON THIS TRIP.


187
00:08:11.768 --> 00:08:13.727
YEAH. I KNOW YOU
WANT TO STAY DRY
FOR A WHILE,


188
00:08:13.770 --> 00:08:15.119
BUT WE JUST
FOUND OUT THAT WE
HAVE LESS TIME


189
00:08:15.163 --> 00:08:17.513
TO MAKE VANCOUVER
THAN RICK THOUGHT.


190
00:08:17.557 --> 00:08:18.862
WE NEED
EXPERIENCED CREW
LIKE YOU.


191
00:08:20.908 --> 00:08:24.433
I WISH I COULD, REALLY,
BUT I PROMISED...


192
00:08:24.476 --> 00:08:25.695
WHO,
YOUR BOYFRIEND?


193
00:08:25.739 --> 00:08:26.696
MY MOTHER.

194
00:08:26.740 --> 00:08:27.784
OH.

195
00:08:27.828 --> 00:08:29.133
SHE'S TRYING TO MAKE UP
FOR LOST TIME,


196
00:08:29.177 --> 00:08:30.657
AND I TOLD HER
I'D HANG AROUND
FOR A WHILE.


197
00:08:30.700 --> 00:08:32.920
JUST 8 DAYS, SUSAN.

198
00:08:32.963 --> 00:08:36.401
8 DAYS. I'LL PAY YOU

199
00:08:36.445 --> 00:08:38.229
WHY ARE YOU SO ANXIOUS?

200
00:08:40.405 --> 00:08:42.625
WELL, THE TRUTH...

201
00:08:42.669 --> 00:08:46.673
UM, I MESSED UP
ON MY LAST JOB.


202
00:08:46.716 --> 00:08:48.109
I MEAN...

203
00:08:48.152 --> 00:08:49.110
MESSED UP.

204
00:08:49.153 --> 00:08:52.113
THERE'S NO NEED
FOR DETAIL.


205
00:08:52.156 --> 00:08:54.245
I WAS GOING
THROUGH A HARD TIME,


206
00:08:54.289 --> 00:08:56.247
LET A FEW THINGS SLIDE,

207
00:08:56.291 --> 00:08:57.684
AND MY REPUTATION SANK.

208
00:09:00.121 --> 00:09:04.125
I NEED THIS ONE
TO RE-ESTABLISH MYSELF.


209
00:09:04.168 --> 00:09:05.648
I'M A GOOD CAPTAIN

210
00:09:05.692 --> 00:09:08.695
WITH DOZENS
OF SUCCESSFUL RUNS
UNDER MY BELT, SUSAN.


211
00:09:08.738 --> 00:09:12.350
MY GOAL IS TO, UH...

212
00:09:12.394 --> 00:09:14.222
IS TO DELIVER EARLY.

213
00:09:14.265 --> 00:09:17.312
PERMISSION TO COME ABOARD!

214
00:09:17.355 --> 00:09:18.574
AYE, AYE, MATEY.

215
00:09:18.618 --> 00:09:20.663
JASON, MY MAN.

216
00:09:20.707 --> 00:09:23.231
HOW ARE YA?
GOOD.


217
00:09:23.274 --> 00:09:24.319
YOU KNOW MATT.

218
00:09:24.362 --> 00:09:25.320
HEY.

219
00:09:25.363 --> 00:09:27.801
AND SUSAN CLARKSON.

220
00:09:27.844 --> 00:09:28.976
SUSAN.

221
00:09:29.019 --> 00:09:31.413
OH, I DIDN'T KNOW
YOU WERE GONNA BE HERE.


222
00:09:31.456 --> 00:09:32.806
JASON, HOW'S IT GOING?

223
00:09:32.849 --> 00:09:33.807
GOOD.

224
00:09:33.850 --> 00:09:35.417
TAKE IT YOU TWO
KNOW EACH OTHER.


225
00:09:35.460 --> 00:09:38.159
YEAH. WELL, KIND OF.
WE GREW UP IN THE SAME TOWN.


226
00:09:38.202 --> 00:09:39.464
SMALL WORLD, HUH?

227
00:09:39.508 --> 00:09:42.337
YEAH, I GUESS IT IS.

228
00:09:42.380 --> 00:09:44.295
SO YOU GONNA BE
CREWING UP WITH US?


229
00:09:44.339 --> 00:09:46.254
I DON'T KNOW.

230
00:09:46.297 --> 00:09:47.647
MAYBE.

231
00:09:56.699 --> 00:09:58.092
Susan: THERE'S NOTHING WORSE

232
00:09:58.135 --> 00:10:00.398
THAN LOOKING FOR A JOB
YOU DON'T WANT.


233
00:10:00.442 --> 00:10:02.618
SAILING'S ALL I CARED ABOUT.

234
00:10:02.662 --> 00:10:06.404
EVERYTHING MY MOTHER HATED
ABOUT IT, I LOVED.


235
00:10:06.448 --> 00:10:08.493
MAYBE THAT WAS PART
OF THE ATTRACTION.


236
00:10:14.761 --> 00:10:16.240
WHY DON'T YOU JUST
GET RID OF THOSE?


237
00:10:16.284 --> 00:10:18.982
BECAUSE I LIKE
TO KNOW I'M STRONGER
THAN THEY ARE.


238
00:10:19.026 --> 00:10:20.941
YOU'RE JUST MAKING IT
HARDER ON YOURSELF.


239
00:10:20.984 --> 00:10:23.378
YOU KNOW WHAT THEY SAY?
YOU SHOULD REMOVE
THE TEMPTATION.


240
00:10:23.421 --> 00:10:25.597
THEY DON'T LIVE MY LIFE.
I DO.


241
00:10:25.641 --> 00:10:27.121
IT'S UP TO ME.

242
00:10:27.164 --> 00:10:29.950
AND YOU KNOW
HOW PROUD I AM OF YOU.


243
00:10:29.993 --> 00:10:32.126
I MEAN, 6 MONTHS SOBER
IS HUGE.


244
00:10:36.347 --> 00:10:37.522
BUT?

245
00:10:37.566 --> 00:10:42.571
BUT IT'S HARD
TO JUST... FORGET.


246
00:10:44.704 --> 00:10:47.402
I'M TRYING.
I REALLY AM.


247
00:10:47.445 --> 00:10:50.100
FOR SO MANY YEARS,
I MEAN...


248
00:10:50.144 --> 00:10:52.668
I CAME HOME NOT KNOWING
WHAT TO EXPECT.


249
00:10:52.712 --> 00:10:56.890
WOULD YOU BE DRUNK,
ANGRY, IRRATIONAL,
PASSED OUT...


250
00:11:00.458 --> 00:11:02.722
OR MY MOTHER?

251
00:11:05.463 --> 00:11:09.990
ALL I CAN SAY IS IT WAS
A VERY DIFFERENT TIME.


252
00:11:10.033 --> 00:11:14.472
I COUNTED ON YOUR FATHER
TO TAKE CARE OF ME,
AND WHEN HE DIDN'T...


253
00:11:14.516 --> 00:11:15.952
MY WORLD FELL APART.

254
00:11:18.520 --> 00:11:22.524
AND THEN I TURNED AROUND
AND DID THE SAME THING
TO YOU.


255
00:11:22.567 --> 00:11:25.527
AND NO MATTER
HOW LONG IT TAKES,


256
00:11:25.570 --> 00:11:26.789
I'M DETERMINED
TO PROVE TO YOU


257
00:11:26.833 --> 00:11:28.878
THAT THINGS
HAVE TRULY CHANGED.


258
00:11:30.053 --> 00:11:31.359
I HOPE THEY HAVE.

259
00:11:34.754 --> 00:11:37.060
THERE'S SOMETHING ELSE.

260
00:11:37.104 --> 00:11:38.583
ISN'T THERE?

261
00:11:40.281 --> 00:11:42.370
YEAH, THERE IS.

262
00:11:45.590 --> 00:11:48.506
HOW WOULD YOU FEEL IF...

263
00:11:48.550 --> 00:11:50.770
IF I WENT AWAY
FOR JUST 2 WEEKS?


264
00:11:52.902 --> 00:11:54.904
LOOK, MOM...
SUSAN.


265
00:11:54.948 --> 00:11:56.340
I KNOW I SAID
WE WOULD STICK AROUND


266
00:11:56.384 --> 00:11:59.213
AND WE COULD WORK THINGS OUT.
WE WILL. I PROMISE.


267
00:11:59.256 --> 00:12:00.431
MOM...

268
00:12:00.475 --> 00:12:02.651
IT'S ONLY A COUPLE
OF WEEKS.


269
00:12:06.394 --> 00:12:08.744
JUST TELL ME ONE THING.
WHAT HAS CHANGED
SINCE THIS MORNING?


270
00:12:08.788 --> 00:12:11.051
NOTHING. NOTHING'S CHANGED.

271
00:12:11.094 --> 00:12:11.921
IT'S JUST...

272
00:12:13.705 --> 00:12:15.838
I NEED TO GO DO THIS.

273
00:12:16.970 --> 00:12:17.840
PLEASE.

274
00:12:21.670 --> 00:12:25.500
YOU'LL CALL ME
EVERY DAY?


275
00:12:25.543 --> 00:12:27.807
ALL RIGHT, ALL RIGHT.
EVERY OTHER DAY.


276
00:12:27.850 --> 00:12:29.939
THAT'S THE BEST
I CAN DO.


277
00:12:31.419 --> 00:12:32.681
DEAL.

278
00:12:35.989 --> 00:12:39.427
♪ EVERY DAY
IS A BRAND-NEW START... ♪


279
00:12:39.470 --> 00:12:42.473
COME ON. YOU GOTTA
NAME ALL 7.


280
00:12:42.517 --> 00:12:44.606
OK, DON'T TELL ME. UH...

281
00:12:44.649 --> 00:12:46.477
SLEEPY, SNEEZY,

282
00:12:46.521 --> 00:12:48.131
DOC...

283
00:12:48.175 --> 00:12:50.351
OH. YEAH, NOW I REMEMBER.

284
00:12:50.394 --> 00:12:51.831
DOPEY.

285
00:12:53.354 --> 00:12:55.835
OH, VERY FUNNY.

286
00:12:55.878 --> 00:12:56.836
VERY FUNNY.

287
00:12:56.879 --> 00:12:59.708
AAH! AAH!

288
00:12:59.751 --> 00:13:01.884
AAH! HEY,
I'M GETTING WET.


289
00:13:01.928 --> 00:13:03.973
ON A BOAT? IMPOSSIBLE.

290
00:13:05.366 --> 00:13:06.933
HEY, SUSAN, COULD
YOU HAND ME THAT
VISE GRIP THERE?


291
00:13:06.976 --> 00:13:08.499
THIS THING'S
ALL GOOFED UP.


292
00:13:08.543 --> 00:13:09.631
SURE.

293
00:13:10.762 --> 00:13:11.720
HERE YOU GO.

294
00:13:11.763 --> 00:13:13.156
THANKS.

295
00:13:13.200 --> 00:13:14.592
LOOKS GOOD. WE'RE DONE.

296
00:13:14.636 --> 00:13:15.376
BREAK TIME.
LET'S GET OUT OF HERE.


297
00:13:15.419 --> 00:13:16.986
WHERE?

298
00:13:17.030 --> 00:13:18.422
WHO CARES?

299
00:13:18.466 --> 00:13:19.728
IT'S A GOOD POINT.

300
00:13:22.862 --> 00:13:25.255
WE'LL BE BACK
IN A LITTLE WHILE, OK?


301
00:13:25.299 --> 00:13:26.430
YEAH, ALL RIGHT.

302
00:13:26.474 --> 00:13:28.041
♪ I DON'T CARE
WHAT THE PEOPLE SAY... ♪


303
00:13:28.084 --> 00:13:29.825
WHOO. THANKS.

304
00:13:29.869 --> 00:13:31.174
OH, I FORGOT
MY SUNGLASSES.


305
00:13:31.218 --> 00:13:32.436
OK.

306
00:13:32.480 --> 00:13:35.962
♪ THE WAY I FEEL,
THEY CAN GET SOME AIR ♪


307
00:13:36.005 --> 00:13:39.443
♪ I KNOW YOU'LL
ALWAYS BE THERE... ♪


308
00:13:39.487 --> 00:13:40.749
SO YOU WANT ME TO STAY
AND HELP YOU OUT?


309
00:13:40.792 --> 00:13:42.446
NO. THIS IS
A ONE-PERSON JOB.


310
00:13:42.490 --> 00:13:43.491
GO ON. HAVE FUN.

311
00:13:43.534 --> 00:13:45.014
YOU'VE EARNED IT.

312
00:13:45.058 --> 00:13:46.450
OK.

313
00:13:46.494 --> 00:13:48.757
I JUST WISH THIS BOAT
WAS IN BETTER SHAPE,
YOU KNOW?


314
00:13:48.800 --> 00:13:50.715
IT LOOKS GOOD,
BUT IT'S LIKE...


315
00:13:50.759 --> 00:13:52.717
HEY, YOU COMING
OR WHAT?


316
00:13:54.981 --> 00:13:56.112
YOU'D BETTER GO.

317
00:13:56.156 --> 00:13:59.159
YEAH, I GUESS I BETTER.
SEE YOU LATER.


318
00:13:59.202 --> 00:14:00.421
SEE YOU LATER.

