320
00:14:06.122 --> 00:14:08.864
Matt: COME ON, SUSAN.
KICK OFF YOUR SHOES.
DANCE A LITTLE.


321
00:14:08.908 --> 00:14:11.475
Susan: ALL RIGHT.
LET'S SEE IF YOU
CAN KEEP UP.


322
00:14:32.670 --> 00:14:35.499
HELLO? DON'T BLOCK MY SUN.

323
00:14:35.543 --> 00:14:37.153
SORRY.

324
00:14:38.807 --> 00:14:40.852
SO WHAT'S THE STOR
WITH YOU AND JASON?


325
00:14:40.896 --> 00:14:42.289
NO STORY.

326
00:14:42.332 --> 00:14:43.899
LET ME GUESS.

327
00:14:43.943 --> 00:14:46.467
PUPPY LOVE
GONE TO THE DOGS.


328
00:14:46.510 --> 00:14:48.904
I DON'T MEAN TO SOUND RUDE,
BUT IT'S REALLY NONE
OF YOUR BUSINESS.


329
00:14:48.948 --> 00:14:51.994
OOH. TOUCHY, TOUCHY.

330
00:14:52.038 --> 00:14:55.041
MUST HAVE BEEN
A REALLY BAD BREAKUP.


331
00:14:55.084 --> 00:14:57.130
EITHER THAT OR HE'S
THE ONE THAT GOT AWAY.


332
00:14:57.173 --> 00:15:00.524
LOOK, JASON AND I
ARE JUST OLD FRIENDS.


333
00:15:00.568 --> 00:15:01.961
WE'VE SAILED TOGETHER,

334
00:15:02.004 --> 00:15:03.571
AND, YES,
WE USED TO BE TOGETHER,


335
00:15:03.614 --> 00:15:05.660
BUT NOW WE'RE BETTER OFF
AS FRIENDS.


336
00:15:05.703 --> 00:15:06.966
WHATEVER YOU SAY.

337
00:15:09.011 --> 00:15:10.926
HEY, COULD YOU
GET ME SOME ICE


338
00:15:10.970 --> 00:15:12.710
AS LONG AS YOU'RE
HEADED BELOW?


339
00:15:12.754 --> 00:15:13.973
[SIGHS]

340
00:15:17.933 --> 00:15:19.152
HMM. HA.

341
00:15:19.195 --> 00:15:23.025
YES, SIR.
I KNOW, SIR.


342
00:15:23.069 --> 00:15:25.549
AT THE LATEST.
THAT'S RIGHT.


343
00:15:25.593 --> 00:15:27.856
YES, YOU CAN.

344
00:15:27.899 --> 00:15:30.337
YOU CAN DEFINITELY
COUNT ON ME, SIR. I...


345
00:15:43.698 --> 00:15:49.878
♪ I JUST CAN'T WAIT FOR
THE CLOCK TO MOVE ITS HANDS ♪


346
00:15:49.921 --> 00:15:50.879
WANT A REFILL ON THAT?

347
00:15:50.922 --> 00:15:52.489
NO, THANKS.

348
00:15:52.533 --> 00:15:55.275
SO WHAT MADE YOU
DO THE WHITBREAD?


349
00:15:55.318 --> 00:15:57.668
WANTED TO SEE IF IT WAS
AS TOUGH AS EVERYONE SAYS.


350
00:15:57.712 --> 00:15:58.626
YEAH? WAS IT?

351
00:15:58.669 --> 00:16:00.106
THERE WERE TIMES.

352
00:16:01.629 --> 00:16:03.892
YEAH, THAT'S GREAT.
THAT TAKES GUTS, YOU KNOW?


353
00:16:03.935 --> 00:16:05.241
YOU GOTTA BE REAL GOOD
TO SURVIVE THAT RACE.


354
00:16:05.285 --> 00:16:10.420
♪ HELP ME UNDERSTAND

355
00:16:10.464 --> 00:16:15.208
♪ WHEN I'M IN YOUR ARMS
I KNOW IT'S RIGHT ♪


356
00:16:17.123 --> 00:16:20.039
♪ WHEN YOU USE
YOUR CHARMS ♪


357
00:16:20.082 --> 00:16:23.346
♪ I JUST WANT YOU
TO HOLD ME TIGHT ♪


358
00:16:23.390 --> 00:16:27.698
♪ IT'S THE WAY
I'M THINKING ABOUT YOU ♪


359
00:16:27.742 --> 00:16:30.092
HEY. I'M GLAD
YOU'RE ALL HERE.


360
00:16:30.136 --> 00:16:31.267
I GOT A LITTLE PIECE
OF NEWS.


361
00:16:31.311 --> 00:16:33.922
I DON'T WANT YOU
TO ALL YELL AT ONCE HERE.


362
00:16:33.965 --> 00:16:35.141
WE'RE GOING TO LEAVE
TOMORROW.


363
00:16:35.184 --> 00:16:36.490
TOMORROW?

364
00:16:36.533 --> 00:16:37.839
WHY THE RUSH?
I HAVEN'T EVEN RUN
A MAINTENANCE...


365
00:16:37.882 --> 00:16:39.449
OWNER WANTS THE BOAT SOONER.

366
00:16:39.493 --> 00:16:41.060
AREN'T WE WAITING
FOR PARTS?


367
00:16:41.103 --> 00:16:42.365
DON'T WORRY ABOUT IT.
I GOT IT COVERED.


368
00:16:42.409 --> 00:16:45.107
THEY'LL BE WAITING
FOR US IN SAN PEDRO.


369
00:16:45.151 --> 00:16:46.804
HERE'S TO THE GOOD SHIP
"SEA-BROOK,"


370
00:16:46.848 --> 00:16:48.328
HER AWARD
-WINNING CREW.

371
00:16:48.371 --> 00:16:50.199
ANYBODY STAYING
FOR DINNER TONIGHT?
I'M BUYING.


372
00:16:50.243 --> 00:16:52.897
♪ DRIVING ME CRAZY...

373
00:16:52.941 --> 00:16:54.725
LIKE THAT.
LIKE THAT.


374
00:16:54.769 --> 00:16:57.989
♪ MY HEART IS BEATING FASTER

375
00:16:58.033 --> 00:17:01.123
♪ TONIGHT THERE'LL BE NO MAZE

376
00:17:01.167 --> 00:17:04.735
♪ SO, HONEY, PLEASE HURRY
HOME AND STAY ♪


377
00:17:04.779 --> 00:17:08.609
♪ THE SUN'S DOWN,
I JUST CAN'T WAIT ♪


378
00:17:08.652 --> 00:17:13.004
♪ LET'S LIVE FOR NOW
AND LEAVE THE REST TO FATE ♪


379
00:17:13.048 --> 00:17:14.005
HI.

380
00:17:14.049 --> 00:17:15.137
HI.

381
00:17:15.181 --> 00:17:17.139
♪ WHEN I'M
IN YOUR ARMS... ♪


382
00:17:17.183 --> 00:17:18.619
IT'S FOR GOOD LUCK
ON THE TRIP.


383
00:17:18.662 --> 00:17:20.447
THANKS.

384
00:17:20.490 --> 00:17:22.579
HEY, HAVE I TOLD YOU
HOW PSYCHED I AM
THAT YOU'RE COMING WITH US?


385
00:17:22.623 --> 00:17:24.581
NOT REALLY.

386
00:17:24.625 --> 00:17:25.452
WELL, I AM.

387
00:17:29.151 --> 00:17:32.111
♪ IT'S THE WAY
I'M THINKING ABOUT YOU ♪


388
00:17:32.154 --> 00:17:34.069
HEY, SUSAN, I NEED YOU...

389
00:17:36.245 --> 00:17:39.248
UH... UH, I'M SORRY.
I DIDN'T...


390
00:17:40.771 --> 00:17:43.687
MEAN TO INTERRUPT.
I NEED YOU BOTH ON THE DOCK.


391
00:17:45.124 --> 00:17:46.603
I'LL TAKE CARE
OF THAT LATER.
DON'T WORRY.


392
00:17:52.131 --> 00:17:54.133
OH, WHAT HAPPENED?

393
00:17:54.176 --> 00:17:55.090
IS HE OK?

394
00:17:55.134 --> 00:17:56.700
YEAH, YEAH,
HE'S FINE.


395
00:17:56.744 --> 00:18:00.095
HE WAS PARTYING HARD
DOWN AT THE ROOST,
GOT INTO A FIGHT.


396
00:18:00.139 --> 00:18:02.445
OH, MAN.
WHERE'S ALLIE?


397
00:18:02.489 --> 00:18:04.447
OH, SHE WENT BACK
TO GET HIS THINGS,
PAY HIS BILL.


398
00:18:04.491 --> 00:18:05.535
COME ON, BUDDY.

399
00:18:05.579 --> 00:18:06.536
RICK.

400
00:18:06.580 --> 00:18:08.234
HE'S A MESS.

401
00:18:08.277 --> 00:18:10.236
YEAH, I KNOW. YEAH,
HE WAS ON THE SHORT END
OF THE FIGHT.


402
00:18:10.279 --> 00:18:12.063
HE'LL BE ALL RIGHT.
COME ON. UP.


403
00:18:15.850 --> 00:18:17.373
THIS IS OUR SKIPPER?

404
00:18:23.118 --> 00:18:24.424
I'M GETTING
A BAD FEELING HERE.


405
00:18:26.556 --> 00:18:28.428
AW, HE WAS PROBABLY
JUST BLOWING OFF STEAM.


406
00:18:28.471 --> 00:18:32.258
WE CANNOT WORRY
ABOUT THIS, OK?


407
00:18:32.301 --> 00:18:33.955
I SAILED UNDER RICK
AT THE FASTNET
LAST AUGUST.


408
00:18:33.998 --> 00:18:36.000
HE DID A GREAT JOB.

409
00:18:36.044 --> 00:18:38.177
I HOPE YOU'RE RIGHT.

410
00:18:38.220 --> 00:18:40.222
HEY, GUYS, WE ALL KNOW
IF PUSH COMES TO SHOVE,


411
00:18:40.266 --> 00:18:41.832
ANY ONE OF US
COULD SKIPPER THIS BOAT.


412
00:18:41.876 --> 00:18:43.269
WELL, THAT'S
CERTAINLY A POINT.


413
00:18:43.312 --> 00:18:45.053
YEAH, SO LET'S NOT
WORRY ABOUT IT.


414
00:18:46.620 --> 00:18:49.362
THIS IS ONE TRIP
WE'RE NEVER GONNA FORGET,
I PROMISE YOU.


415
00:19:14.343 --> 00:19:16.127
♪ WHEN I WAS YOUNG,
SO VERY YOUNG ♪


416
00:19:16.171 --> 00:19:18.434
♪ I DIDN'T HAVE A HERO

417
00:19:18.478 --> 00:19:20.175
♪ TOO MUCH TIME
AND NOT ENOUGH GOALS ♪


418
00:19:20.219 --> 00:19:22.569
♪ HANGING WITH THE ZEROES

419
00:19:22.612 --> 00:19:24.745
♪ STILL, I COULDN'T
STOP MYSELF ♪


420
00:19:24.788 --> 00:19:26.573
♪ FROM CHASING
EMPTY SHADOWS ♪


421
00:19:26.616 --> 00:19:29.228
♪ NOW IT SEEMS
I'VE LOST THEM AGAIN... ♪


422
00:19:29.271 --> 00:19:31.578
ALLIE, SUSAN,
PHOTO TIME.


423
00:19:31.621 --> 00:19:33.319
SELF-TIMER'S
IN THE BAG.


424
00:19:33.362 --> 00:19:36.670
♪ THE REASONS
WHY I'M LEAVING ♪


425
00:19:36.713 --> 00:19:39.107
♪ I JUST KNOW I'VE GOT TO GO

426
00:19:39.150 --> 00:19:42.763
♪ IF I CANNOT BE HERE

427
00:19:42.806 --> 00:19:44.678
♪ I'D JUST BE
SOMEWHERE ELSE ♪


428
00:19:44.721 --> 00:19:46.984
♪ SITTING WITH THAT
AND THAT'S A FACT ♪


429
00:19:47.028 --> 00:19:48.986
WHOO!

430
00:19:49.030 --> 00:19:50.161
♪ LOST MY MIND
A COUPLE OF TIMES ♪


431
00:19:50.205 --> 00:19:51.815
♪ AT LEAST I THOUGHT I DID

432
00:19:51.859 --> 00:19:54.165
♪ YOU'D THINK BY NOW
I'D SEEN THOSE SIGNS ♪


433
00:19:54.209 --> 00:19:56.298
♪ AND KEEP FIGHTIN'
WITH MY HEAD ♪


434
00:19:56.342 --> 00:19:58.387
♪ STILL, I COULDN'T
STOP MYSELF ♪


435
00:19:58.431 --> 00:20:00.433
♪ FROM CHASING
ALL THOSE RAINBOWS ♪


436
00:20:00.476 --> 00:20:02.435
♪ LOOKING FOR
THAT POT OF GOLD ♪


437
00:20:02.478 --> 00:20:05.046
♪ ALL I FOUND IS I GOT OLD

438
00:20:05.089 --> 00:20:09.180
♪ I DON'T WANT REASONS WHY...

439
00:20:24.935 --> 00:20:26.502
[ALARM CLOCK BEEPS]

440
00:20:26.546 --> 00:20:29.592
♪ I'M WONDERIN'

441
00:20:30.854 --> 00:20:36.338
♪ WHAT I'M DOIN'

442
00:20:36.382 --> 00:20:40.995
♪ I'M FEELIN'

443
00:20:41.038 --> 00:20:44.041
♪ OUT OF PLACE...

444
00:20:44.085 --> 00:20:45.042
I HATE NIGHT SHIFTS.

445
00:20:45.086 --> 00:20:47.175
THERE'S COFFEE
IN THERE.


446
00:20:47.218 --> 00:20:48.481
I COULD USE IT.

447
00:20:53.312 --> 00:20:55.705
WOW. THAT'S AMAZING.

448
00:20:55.749 --> 00:20:57.446
WHAT?

449
00:20:57.490 --> 00:20:59.970
I'D HAVE POLISH
HALFWAY UP MY LEG.


450
00:21:00.014 --> 00:21:02.408
JUST A MATTER
OF PRACTICE.


451
00:21:02.451 --> 00:21:03.931
YOU WANT TO TRY?

452
00:21:03.974 --> 00:21:05.976
THOSE NAILS COULD
USE SOME COLOR.


453
00:21:06.020 --> 00:21:07.630
WHY BOTHER?

454
00:21:07.674 --> 00:21:09.719
NOBODY NOTICES MY TOES.

455
00:21:09.763 --> 00:21:11.808
OH, I'D SAY
THERE ARE A COUPLE
