00:21:38.531 --> 00:21:39.619
YOU UP LATE?

467
00:21:39.662 --> 00:21:40.924
NOT REALLY.

468
00:21:44.667 --> 00:21:46.582
YOU SHOULD GET
SOME SLEEP.


469
00:21:46.626 --> 00:21:48.976
THE MIDNIGHT WATCH
IS A SOLO GIG
IF I REMEMBER CORRECTLY.


470
00:21:49.019 --> 00:21:50.107
YEAH.

471
00:21:52.719 --> 00:21:55.417
OK.

472
00:21:55.461 --> 00:21:58.420
♪ I'M WONDERIN'

473
00:21:58.464 --> 00:21:59.421
GOOD NIGHT.

474
00:21:59.465 --> 00:22:00.291
NIGHT.

475
00:22:00.335 --> 00:22:04.513
♪ HOW I'M FEELIN'

476
00:22:06.167 --> 00:22:10.345
♪ YOUR CHARMS

477
00:22:10.389 --> 00:22:16.569
♪ COME AND GO

478
00:22:16.612 --> 00:22:21.225
♪ IT'S HARD TO DECIDE

479
00:22:21.269 --> 00:22:24.577
♪ THERE'S NO EASY ROAD

480
00:22:29.277 --> 00:22:30.887
WHERE ARE WE DOCKING
IN SAN PEDRO?


481
00:22:30.931 --> 00:22:31.888
THE END TIE.

482
00:22:31.932 --> 00:22:33.150
[ALARM SOUNDS]

483
00:22:33.194 --> 00:22:34.935
Jason: HEY, RICK!
GOT A PROBLEM DOWN HERE!


484
00:22:34.978 --> 00:22:36.066
SOUNDS LIKE HE'S
IN THE ENGINE ROOM.


485
00:22:36.110 --> 00:22:37.111
ALL RIGHT.
HOLD HER, SUSAN.


486
00:22:42.072 --> 00:22:44.597
SHE'S SLIPPING!

487
00:22:48.818 --> 00:22:50.124
OH, MAN.

488
00:22:50.167 --> 00:22:51.995
WE GOTTA GET
SOME SAIL UP.


489
00:22:52.039 --> 00:22:54.911
Susan: THE CURRENT'S
DRAGGING US INTO THE DOCK.


490
00:22:54.955 --> 00:22:56.565
IT'S JAMMED!

491
00:22:56.609 --> 00:22:57.653
UHH!

492
00:23:00.961 --> 00:23:02.876
WE'RE GONNA HIT THE DOCK!

493
00:23:02.919 --> 00:23:03.877
MATT!

494
00:23:03.920 --> 00:23:05.487
MATT, GET UP HERE!

495
00:23:05.531 --> 00:23:07.184
I'M HERE. I'M HERE.
TAKE THE HELM.


496
00:23:07.228 --> 00:23:09.143
I'M GONNA GO LET
THE JIB OUT.


497
00:23:11.101 --> 00:23:13.147
Matt: GET IT OUT QUICK!
Jason: I AM!


498
00:23:13.190 --> 00:23:14.540
GET THE STERN!

499
00:23:14.583 --> 00:23:15.497
HURRY, JASON!

500
00:23:15.541 --> 00:23:17.456
GO! GO! GO!
COME ON, JASON!


501
00:23:21.547 --> 00:23:23.070
WATCH IT!
HEY, WATCH OUT!


502
00:23:23.113 --> 00:23:24.506
GET OUT OF THE WAY!

503
00:23:30.251 --> 00:23:31.992
COME ON.

504
00:23:34.951 --> 00:23:36.300
TOO CLOSE.

505
00:23:36.344 --> 00:23:37.998
Susan: GET READY
TO FEND OFF.


506
00:23:42.306 --> 00:23:44.004
Jason: LOOKS LIKE
WE'RE GONNA MAKE IT.


507
00:23:47.050 --> 00:23:48.269
YEAH!

508
00:23:49.313 --> 00:23:50.227
WHOO.

509
00:23:50.271 --> 00:23:51.881
CAN YOU BELIEVE THAT?

510
00:23:53.883 --> 00:23:55.494
I THOUGHT
WE WERE TOAST.


511
00:23:58.758 --> 00:23:59.976
WHAT HAPPENED?

512
00:24:00.020 --> 00:24:02.413
IMPELLER WENT,
ENGINE OVERHEATED.


513
00:24:06.853 --> 00:24:08.115
WE'RE IN SAN PEDRO.

514
00:24:08.158 --> 00:24:09.290
Patricia:
IS EVERYTHING ALL RIGHT?


515
00:24:09.333 --> 00:24:10.944
GREAT. WE'RE
MAKING GOOD TIME.


516
00:24:10.987 --> 00:24:14.556
GOOD. I'M... I'M SORRY
I GOT SO ANGRY, SUSAN.


517
00:24:14.600 --> 00:24:16.123
I JUST... I DON'T KNOW...

518
00:24:16.166 --> 00:24:17.690
I HATE IT WHEN
I GET LIKE THAT.


519
00:24:17.733 --> 00:24:18.734
I KNOW.

520
00:24:18.778 --> 00:24:20.606
SO WHEN DO YOU
THINK YOU'LL BE BACK?


521
00:24:20.649 --> 00:24:22.390
DEPENDS ON WHAT
THE OWNER HAS PLANNED.


522
00:24:22.433 --> 00:24:24.610
CAN'T BE SOON
ENOUGH FOR ME.


523
00:24:24.653 --> 00:24:26.350
MOM, LOOK, I GOTTA GO.

524
00:24:26.394 --> 00:24:27.787
I'LL CALL YOU FROM
MY NEXT STOP IN 2 DAYS, OK?


525
00:24:27.830 --> 00:24:29.049
TAKE CARE.
I LOVE YOU.


526
00:24:29.092 --> 00:24:31.094
LOVE YOU, TOO.

527
00:24:31.138 --> 00:24:32.226
HOW'S MOM?

528
00:24:32.269 --> 00:24:35.185
FINE, BUT SHE
WORRIES TOO MUCH.


529
00:24:35.229 --> 00:24:37.710
I DIDN'T TELL HER
HOW WE ARRIVED
IN SAN PEDRO.


530
00:24:37.753 --> 00:24:38.885
THAT SHOULD HAVE
NEVER HAPPENED.


531
00:24:38.928 --> 00:24:40.843
RICK SHOULD HAVE
TAKEN CARE OF THAT.


532
00:24:40.887 --> 00:24:42.366
DID YOU TELL HIM?

533
00:24:42.410 --> 00:24:44.760
YEAH, I TOLD HIM
THE IMPELLER SHAFT
WAS RUSTY, YEAH.


534
00:24:44.804 --> 00:24:47.284
WELL, THAT IS
ONE OF THE PARTS
WE HAVE WAITING HERE.


535
00:24:47.328 --> 00:24:48.503
RICK NEVER SAID
IT WAS URGENT.


536
00:24:48.547 --> 00:24:50.897
I JUST FIGURED
IT WAS ROUTINE UPKEEP.


537
00:24:50.940 --> 00:24:53.073
IT WOULDN'T HAVE MATTERED
IF THE ENGINE HADN'T
OVERHEATED, REALLY.


538
00:24:53.116 --> 00:24:54.335
THAT'S NOT
THE POINT.


539
00:24:54.378 --> 00:24:55.684
I MEAN, RICK
DROPPED THE BALL.


540
00:24:55.728 --> 00:24:57.643
HOW MUCH DO WE
REALLY KNOW ABOUT
THIS GUY ANYWAY?


541
00:24:57.686 --> 00:24:59.253
LOOK, GUYS,

542
00:24:59.296 --> 00:25:00.820
I'VE SAILED
WITH HIM, OK?


543
00:25:00.863 --> 00:25:01.995
AND I'VE
HUNG OUT WITH HIM
AT THE ROOST.


544
00:25:02.038 --> 00:25:03.649
HE SEEMS OK TO ME.

545
00:25:03.692 --> 00:25:05.781
LOOK, THE BOTTOM LINE IS
WITH US CREWING FOR HIM,


546
00:25:05.825 --> 00:25:08.915
HE'S GONNA BE FINE.
NO MATTER WHAT,
HE'S GONNA BE FINE.


547
00:25:08.958 --> 00:25:12.135
YOU'RE RIGHT. WE'RE
ACTING LIKE THIS IS
SOME TRIP AROUND THE WORLD.


548
00:25:12.179 --> 00:25:13.702
COME ON. WE'D BETTER
HURRY UP AND GET
THOSE PARTS.


549
00:25:13.746 --> 00:25:15.225
HE WANTS TO
SHOVE OFF
RIGHT AFTER DINNER.


550
00:25:23.625 --> 00:25:26.410
I LIKED COLLEGE, BUT
I JUST COULDN'T HELP IT.


551
00:25:26.454 --> 00:25:28.587
I HAD TO GET AWAY, SAIL.

552
00:25:30.197 --> 00:25:32.765
I'M SORRY, BUT LIVING
ON ONE OF THESE THINGS
FOR 3 YEARS


553
00:25:32.808 --> 00:25:35.115
SOUNDS LIKE
A LIVING NIGHTMARE.


554
00:25:35.158 --> 00:25:37.204
AND FOR ME, IT WAS
A DREAM COME TRUE.


555
00:25:39.336 --> 00:25:41.904
YOU NEVER FEEL LIKE
YOU'RE IN PRISON,


556
00:25:41.948 --> 00:25:44.211
JUST TOTALLY CUT OFF
FROM REALITY?


557
00:25:44.254 --> 00:25:46.300
NO ONE CAN TELL ME
WHAT TO DO HERE...


558
00:25:46.343 --> 00:25:49.085
OR PULL ON ME.

559
00:25:49.129 --> 00:25:51.610
SOMEDAY I WANT TO SAIL SOLO
ACROSS THE PACIFIC.


560
00:25:52.872 --> 00:25:55.135
HEY, ALLIE, HOW ABOUT
MAKING SOME SANDWICHES?


561
00:25:55.178 --> 00:25:57.528
I'M NOT HUNGRY.

562
00:25:57.572 --> 00:25:59.618
Rick: WELL, WE ARE.
COME ON. HELP OUT A LITTLE.


563
00:25:59.661 --> 00:26:00.619
YOU DO IT.

564
00:26:00.662 --> 00:26:02.142
I'M ON WATCH.

565
00:26:02.185 --> 00:26:04.535
SO THAT MAKES ME THE COOK?

566
00:26:04.579 --> 00:26:06.363
I DON'T THINK SO, RICK.

567
00:26:06.407 --> 00:26:07.756
I'LL MAKE 'EM.

568
00:26:07.800 --> 00:26:10.237
NO, NO.
ALLIE WILL DO IT.


569
00:26:10.280 --> 00:26:11.499
FORGET IT.

570
00:26:11.542 --> 00:26:13.414
YOU'RE PART
OF THIS CREW.


571
00:26:13.457 --> 00:26:15.024
IT MEANS YOU WORK
LIKE EVERYBODY ELSE.


572
00:26:15.068 --> 00:26:17.766
SLEEPING WITH YOU
IS PLENTY OF WORK.


573
00:26:19.768 --> 00:26:21.509
YOU ALWAYS
PULL THIS CRAP.


574
00:26:24.817 --> 00:26:27.776
I SWEAR, ALLIE,
YOU'RE NOT GONNA
RUIN THIS JOB, TOO.


575
00:26:32.259 --> 00:26:34.435
IT IS SO TYPICAL
OF RICK TO BLAME ME


576
00:26:34.478 --> 00:26:35.958
FOR GETTING FIRED
OFF HIS LAST BOAT.


577
00:26:36.002 --> 00:26:39.396
HE KNEW THE OWNER DIDN'T
ALLOW DRINKING ON BOARD.


578
00:26:41.137 --> 00:26:42.486
WHAT'S WITH YOU TWO?

579
00:26:42.530 --> 00:26:44.053
YOU SEEM SO DIFFERENT,

580
00:26:44.097 --> 00:26:46.926
I CAN'T FIGURE OUT
WHY YOU'RE TOGETHER.


581
00:26:46.969 --> 00:26:49.493
RICK HELPED ME
WHEN I SPLIT UP
WITH MY HUSBAND.


582
00:26:49.537 --> 00:26:51.713
IT GOT PRETTY UGLY.

583
00:26:51.757 --> 00:26:53.019
I DIDN'T KNOW
YOU WERE MARRIED.


584
00:26:53.062 --> 00:26:54.411
YEAH.

585
00:26:58.764 --> 00:27:01.723
RICK'S A SWEET GUY
WHO LOVES ME


586
00:27:01.767 --> 00:27:03.420
AND DOESN'T
EXPECT MUCH,


587
00:27:03.464 --> 00:27:05.205
AND THAT'S
JUST WHAT I NEED


588
00:27:05.248 --> 00:27:07.511
TILL I GET TO CANADA
TO START OVER.


589
00:27:07.555 --> 00:27:09.035
AND HE'S OK WITH THAT?

590
00:27:10.253 --> 00:27:13.082
EVERY RELATIONSHIP
DOESN'T HAVE TO BE
A LIFELONG COMMITMENT.


591
00:27:18.435 --> 00:27:20.437
LOOK. DOLPHINS.

592
00:27:22.309 --> 00:27:23.484
THOSE AREN'T DOLPHINS.

593
00:27:26.139 --> 00:27:27.357
THEY'RE SHARKS.

594
00:27:57.605 --> 00:27:59.825
MMM. MMM.

595
00:27:59.868 --> 00:28:01.565
I THOUGHT YOU
WERE GETTING COFFEE.


596
00:28:01.609 --> 00:28:02.958
THAT'S
TOO MUCH TROUBLE.


597
00:28:03.002 --> 00:28:04.438
AND I THOUGHT
THIS WAS A DRY BOAT.


598
00:28:04.481 --> 00:28:06.179
IT'S JUST A LITTLE WHISKEY
I BROUGHT FOR COLD NIGHTS.


599
00:28:06.222 --> 00:28:07.310
IT WON'T HURT ANYTHING.

600
00:28:07.354 --> 00:28:10.357
I DON'T DRINK
WHEN I'M ON WATCH.


601
00:28:11.488 --> 00:28:14.491
OH, AND YOU'VE NEVER
DONE 60 IN A 55?


602
00:28:14.535 --> 00:28:15.623
IT'S NOT THE SAME.

603
00:28:18.104 --> 00:28:19.235
AHH.

604
00:28:19.279 --> 00:28:20.367
OK.

605
00:28:21.324 --> 00:28:22.586
YOU'RE RIGHT.

606
00:28:22.630 --> 00:28:23.718
I'M SORRY.

607
00:28:25.285 --> 00:28:26.808
DON'T MENTION IT
TO RICK, OK?


608
00:28:29.855 --> 00:28:32.466
I GUESS I, UH...

609
00:28:32.509 --> 00:28:33.946
I ALSO DRINK
SOMETIMES WHEN
I'M NERVOUS.


610
00:28:33.989 --> 00:28:35.861
IT TAKES
THE EDGE OFF.


611
00:28:35.904 --> 00:28:36.992
WHAT ARE YOU NERVOUS ABOUT?

612
00:28:40.256 --> 00:28:41.910
YOU.

613
00:28:41.954 --> 00:28:43.042
AND ME. US.

614
00:28:43.085 --> 00:28:45.435
US?

615
00:28:45.479 --> 00:28:47.873
YEAH, YOU KNOW
WHAT I MEAN.


616
00:28:47.916 --> 00:28:50.310
THE OTHER NIGHT
BEFORE WE LEFT
SAN DIEGO.


617
00:28:50.353 --> 00:28:52.486
YEAH, I REMEMBER.

618
00:28:52.529 --> 00:28:53.879
LOOK, MATT...

619
00:28:53.922 --> 00:28:55.358
I LIKE YOU A LOT,

620
00:28:55.402 --> 00:28:57.056
BUT I JUST CAN'T...

621
00:28:58.579 --> 00:28:59.841
IT'S JASON, ISN'T IT?

622
00:28:59.885 --> 00:29:01.669
THERE'S A STORY THERE.
I KNOW IT.


623
00:29:01.712 --> 00:29:03.976
WHAT? NO. I WAS
GONNA SAY I'M WARY


624
00:29:04.019 --> 00:29:05.716
ABOUT GETTING INVOLVED
WITH SOMEONE I'M SAILING WITH.


625
00:29:05.760 --> 00:29:07.936
HMM. DIDN'T SEEM TO BE
A PROBLEM WITH HIM.


626
00:29:07.980 --> 00:29:11.592
A PERFECT EXAMPLE
OF WHY I'M WARY.


627
00:29:17.467 --> 00:29:20.862
HEY. I'M SORRY.
I'M...


628
00:29:20.906 --> 00:29:22.385
BEING A JERK.

629
00:29:23.691 --> 00:29:24.866
GIVE ME ANOTHER CHANCE.

630
00:29:31.220 --> 00:29:33.222
MATT, LOOK,
I DIDN'T...


631
00:29:33.266 --> 00:29:35.877
NO, DON'T... DON'T WORRY.
YOU DON'T HAVE TO
SPELL IT OUT, OK?


632
00:29:35.921 --> 00:29:39.576
IF YOU WANT TO GO OFF
AND RELIGHT SOME FIRE
WITH JASON,


633
00:29:39.620 --> 00:29:42.057
THAT'S FINE.
THAT'S FINE, REALLY.


634
00:29:42.101 --> 00:29:44.538
I GOTTA GO. I GOTTA
GO GET SOMETHING.


635
00:29:44.581 --> 00:29:46.018
NO, MATT, LOOK,
I DON'T...


636
00:29:54.504 --> 00:29:57.899
IT'S ONE AFTERNOON, RICK,
A COUPLE OF HOURS.


637
00:29:57.943 --> 00:30:00.684
BESIDES, IT WAS 4-1.
YOU LOST.


638
00:30:00.728 --> 00:30:03.296
AS IF THIS WERE
A DEMOCRACY.


639
00:30:03.339 --> 00:30:04.906
WHERE'D YOU FIND
THIS PLACE
ANYWAY?


640
00:30:04.950 --> 00:30:07.909
FRIENDS OF MINE AND I
STUMBLED ACROSS IT
A FEW YEARS AGO.


641
00:30:07.953 --> 00:30:10.781
OWNER HAS A HOUSE
ON THE OTHER SIDE,
BUT HE'S NEVER HOME.


642
00:30:10.825 --> 00:30:11.870
Allie: COME ON.

643
00:30:13.436 --> 00:30:15.569
HMM?

644
00:30:15.612 --> 00:30:18.137
COME ON. TAKE
SOME CHANCES, RICK.


645
00:30:18.180 --> 00:30:19.747
BEAUTIFUL ISLAND.

646
00:30:21.836 --> 00:30:23.533
[EXCITED CHATTER]

647
00:30:23.577 --> 00:30:26.710
♪ THE SUN IS LOW

648
00:30:26.754 --> 00:30:31.672
♪ STILL, THE PEOPLE
WHO SEE IS WHERE I BELONG ♪


649
00:30:31.715 --> 00:30:34.849
♪ LET THE WAVES...

650
00:30:34.893 --> 00:30:37.025
NOW, THIS...
THIS IS BEAUTIFUL.


651
00:30:37.069 --> 00:30:41.725
♪ I KNOW THEY'LL TAKE ME
OUT TO SEA AGAIN ♪


652
00:30:41.769 --> 00:30:45.816
♪ LET THE WAVES...

653
00:30:45.860 --> 00:30:46.817
YO, RICK.

654
00:30:46.861 --> 00:30:48.689
♪ HELP ME TO SEE...

655
00:30:48.732 --> 00:30:49.951
WHEN DO YOU WANNA
TURN THIS PUPPY IN?


656
00:30:49.995 --> 00:30:52.171
I THINK WE CAN
BE THERE IN 5 DAYS.


657
00:30:52.214 --> 00:30:54.564
WOW. THAT'S PRETTY FAST.

658
00:30:54.608 --> 00:30:56.392
ARE YOU SURE WE CAN?

659
00:30:56.436 --> 00:30:58.655
YES, I'M SURE.

660
00:30:58.699 --> 00:30:59.569
HEY, UH...

661
00:30:59.613 --> 00:31:01.180
RICK, AT THAT PACE,

662
00:31:01.223 --> 00:31:02.616
WE'RE GONNA HAVE TO WORK
AROUND THE CLOCK JUST TO...


663
00:31:02.659 --> 00:31:04.835
I SAID I'M SURE.

664
00:31:04.879 --> 00:31:06.446
DON'T WORRY
ABOUT IT.


665
00:31:06.489 --> 00:31:08.622
LOOK, WE GET THERE
ON TIME,


666
00:31:08.665 --> 00:31:10.058
BONUSES ALL AROUND.

667
00:31:13.148 --> 00:31:17.065
♪ LET THE WAVES COME
ROLLIN' IN ♪


668
00:31:17.109 --> 00:31:23.115
♪ 'CAUSE I KNOW THEY'LL
TAKE ME OUT TO SEA AGAIN ♪


669
00:31:23.158 --> 00:31:27.771
♪ LET THE WAVES WASH
MY CARES AWAY... ♪


670
00:31:27.815 --> 00:31:29.860
HEY.
IS THIS SEAT TAKEN?


671
00:31:29.904 --> 00:31:31.297
NOPE. ALL YOURS.

672
00:31:32.733 --> 00:31:34.778
AHH.

673
00:31:34.822 --> 00:31:36.432
WHEW. HOW'S IT GOING?

674
00:31:36.476 --> 00:31:38.260
ALL RIGHT.

675
00:31:40.088 --> 00:31:41.742
RICK'S MAKING ME
A LITTLE NERVOUS.


676
00:31:41.785 --> 00:31:44.005
IT'S LIKE HE'S
ON A MISSION
OR SOMETHING.


677
00:31:44.049 --> 00:31:46.486
YEAH. YEAH,
I KNOW WHAT YOU MEAN.


678
00:31:46.529 --> 00:31:49.576
LOOKS LIKE WE'LL BE WORKING
HARDER THAN WE PLANNED.


679
00:31:51.056 --> 00:31:52.231
AT LEAST IT'S
A SHORT TRIP.


680
00:31:57.584 --> 00:32:00.891
SO, MATT, MATT SEEMS
LIKE A NICE ENOUGH GUY, HUH?


681
00:32:00.935 --> 00:32:03.894
YEAH. HE'S A LITTLE
HYPER SOMETIMES,
BUT HE MEANS WELL.


682
00:32:05.809 --> 00:32:06.767
HOW LONG HAVE YOU KNOWN HIM?

683
00:32:06.810 --> 00:32:09.639
A FEW MONTHS,
MAYBE MORE.


684
00:32:10.553 --> 00:32:11.641
HOW COME?

685
00:32:14.079 --> 00:32:17.952
OH, UM, I DON'T KNOW, UM...

686
00:32:17.996 --> 00:32:19.388
I GUESS...

687
00:32:19.432 --> 00:32:22.478
I GUESS I REMEMBER
A TIME WHEN, UH...


688
00:32:22.522 --> 00:32:24.437
WHEN I WAS THE ONE
YOU WERE LOOKING AT.


689
00:32:24.480 --> 00:32:26.091
I'M NOT LOOKING
AT MATT.


690
00:32:27.918 --> 00:32:29.398
I APPRECIATE THAT,
BUT YOU DON'T NEED


691
00:32:29.442 --> 00:32:31.574
TO PROTECT ME,
YOU KNOW?
I ALREADY KNOW.


692
00:32:31.618 --> 00:32:33.402
KNOW?

693
00:32:33.446 --> 00:32:36.231
I SAW YOU
THE OTHER NIGHT
IN THE COCKPIT.


694
00:32:36.275 --> 00:32:37.493
WELL, THEN YOU
MISSED THE PART


695
00:32:37.537 --> 00:32:39.452
WHERE I SAID
I JUST WANT
TO BE FRIENDS.


696
00:32:41.193 --> 00:32:42.237
REALLY?

