704
00:33:00.168 --> 00:33:01.300
I JUST
KEPT THINKING,


705
00:33:01.343 --> 00:33:03.171
MAYBE THIS MEANS
THAT WE CAN STILL,
UH...


706
00:33:17.490 --> 00:33:19.970
I'M SORRY.
I MEAN, THAT'S...
THAT WASN'T RIGHT.


707
00:33:20.014 --> 00:33:22.103
JUST BECAUSE YOU'RE
NOT INTERESTED IN
MATT DOESN'T MEAN...


708
00:33:22.147 --> 00:33:25.063
IT'S NOT THAT, JASON.
LOOK...


709
00:33:25.106 --> 00:33:26.542
I THOUGHT
ABOUT YOU, TOO,


710
00:33:26.586 --> 00:33:29.763
A LOT, BUT...

711
00:33:29.806 --> 00:33:32.679
THE REASON
WE BROKE UP...


712
00:33:32.722 --> 00:33:34.115
IT'S STILL THERE.

713
00:33:36.465 --> 00:33:38.424
THE REASON
I NEVER UNDERSTOOD,
I REMEMBER.


714
00:33:38.467 --> 00:33:40.121
I JUST WASN'T READY
FOR WHAT YOU WANTED.


715
00:33:40.165 --> 00:33:43.255
ALL I WANTED WAS...

716
00:33:43.298 --> 00:33:45.126
WAS YOU, SUSAN.
THAT'S IT.


717
00:33:47.781 --> 00:33:50.349
I KNOW.
I WANTED THAT, TOO,


718
00:33:50.392 --> 00:33:52.351
BUT EVERY TIME I THOUGHT
ABOUT THE FUTURE, YOU KNOW,


719
00:33:52.394 --> 00:33:53.787
US BEING TOGETHER...

720
00:33:55.267 --> 00:33:58.879
I JUST WASN'T READY
FOR THAT KIND OF COMMITMENT.


721
00:33:58.922 --> 00:34:00.010
YEAH.

722
00:34:06.234 --> 00:34:08.236
I MISS MY BEST FRIEND,
THOUGH.


723
00:34:08.280 --> 00:34:10.543
ME, TOO.

724
00:34:10.586 --> 00:34:12.197
I'M GLAD
YOU'RE HERE.


725
00:34:24.774 --> 00:34:27.212
MATT, BUDDY,
WHAT'S WRONG?


726
00:34:27.255 --> 00:34:29.953
HUH? NOTHING.

727
00:34:29.997 --> 00:34:31.912
LET'S JUST SAY
I'M AS ANXIOUS


728
00:34:31.955 --> 00:34:33.218
TO GET TO VANCOUVER
AS YOU ARE.


729
00:34:35.698 --> 00:34:37.222
[THUNDER]

730
00:35:29.665 --> 00:35:31.667
HEY, MATT.

731
00:35:31.711 --> 00:35:32.799
GRAB SOME REST.

732
00:35:32.842 --> 00:35:34.627
ME AND SUSAN
ARE UP FOR
THE NIGHT SHIFT.


733
00:35:34.670 --> 00:35:36.150
YEAH.
I BET YOU ARE.


734
00:35:36.194 --> 00:35:37.717
WHAT'S THAT
SUPPOSED TO MEAN?


735
00:35:37.760 --> 00:35:39.066
NOTHING.

736
00:35:39.109 --> 00:35:41.808
STAY OUTTA MY FACE, OK?

737
00:35:41.851 --> 00:35:45.203
IS THIS ABOUT SUSAN?

738
00:35:45.246 --> 00:35:47.553
'CAUSE IF IT IS,
YOU'RE WAY OFF,
MATT.


739
00:35:47.596 --> 00:35:49.119
THIS IS...

740
00:35:49.163 --> 00:35:52.514
WE'RE JUST TRYING
TO PATCH UP AN OLD
FRIENDSHIP, OK?


741
00:35:52.558 --> 00:35:53.863
THAT'S IT.

742
00:35:53.907 --> 00:35:56.126
HA. WELL,
IF THAT'S WHAT YOU
REALLY THINK, JASON,


743
00:35:56.170 --> 00:35:57.867
YOU'RE DUMBER
THAN I THOUGHT.


744
00:35:58.955 --> 00:36:02.481
LOOK, WE GOT
A LONG WAY
TO GO, MATT.


745
00:36:02.524 --> 00:36:05.962
OK? LET'S JUST
FORGET ABOUT THIS.
LET'S JUST...


746
00:36:06.006 --> 00:36:08.574
LET'S JUST
DROP IT.


747
00:36:08.617 --> 00:36:09.879
ALL RIGHT?

748
00:36:09.923 --> 00:36:12.273
ARE WE COOL?

749
00:36:12.317 --> 00:36:13.796
YEAH, WE'RE COOL.

750
00:36:13.840 --> 00:36:15.058
ALL RIGHT.

751
00:36:15.102 --> 00:36:16.538
JUST STAY OUTTA MY FACE.

752
00:36:55.838 --> 00:36:57.710
SOMETHING WRONG?

753
00:36:57.753 --> 00:36:59.320
WELL, BAROMETER'S
DROPPING,


754
00:36:59.364 --> 00:37:01.931
WHICH USUALLY MEANS
A STORM'S COMING,


755
00:37:01.975 --> 00:37:03.977
BUT THE WEATHER SERVICE
PREDICTED CLEAR SKIES,


756
00:37:04.020 --> 00:37:06.980
PLUS I CAN'T FIND
THIS ONE CHART.


757
00:37:07.023 --> 00:37:08.503
YOU MEAN WE'RE LOST?

758
00:37:10.375 --> 00:37:11.854
NO. WE'RE NOT LOST.

759
00:37:11.898 --> 00:37:14.292
I JUST... I WAS
WONDERING HOW MUCH
TIME WE COULD SAVE


760
00:37:14.335 --> 00:37:17.643
BY SKIPPING
OUR PIT STOP
AT MORRO BAY.


761
00:37:19.862 --> 00:37:20.994
HEY...

762
00:37:22.778 --> 00:37:26.391
DON'T PUT
SO MUCH PRESSURE
ON YOURSELF, OK?


763
00:37:26.434 --> 00:37:29.829
NOT EVERYTHING
IS RIDING ON
THIS ONE JOB.


764
00:37:29.872 --> 00:37:31.309
YEAH, I KNOW.

765
00:37:34.747 --> 00:37:36.226
DON'T WORRY, OK?

766
00:37:38.490 --> 00:37:40.579
I'M FINE.

767
00:37:40.622 --> 00:37:44.322
IT'S ALL GONNA BE...
FINE.


768
00:37:53.418 --> 00:37:55.028
COME ON.

769
00:37:55.071 --> 00:37:57.813
[THUNDER]

770
00:38:01.469 --> 00:38:03.819
WHERE'D ALL THIS
WEATHER COME FROM?


771
00:38:03.863 --> 00:38:05.255
DON'T KNOW.

772
00:38:05.299 --> 00:38:06.735
LAST REPORT
SAID CONDITIONS WERE
SUPPOSED TO BE GOOD.


773
00:38:06.779 --> 00:38:09.172
HEH. THAT'S
OUR TAX DOLLARS
HARD AT WORK.


774
00:38:09.216 --> 00:38:10.304
MAYBE WE SHOULD STAY
IN MORRO BAY


775
00:38:10.348 --> 00:38:11.479
UNTIL WE SEE
WHAT THIS TURNS INTO.


776
00:38:11.523 --> 00:38:12.611
WE'RE NOT GOING
TO MORRO BAY.


777
00:38:12.654 --> 00:38:14.526
WE PASSED THE CHANNEL
ABOUT AN HOUR AGO.


778
00:38:14.569 --> 00:38:16.179
WE WHAT?
WHY?


779
00:38:16.223 --> 00:38:18.225
'CAUSE I MADE A DECISION
BASED ON THE REPORTS.


780
00:38:18.268 --> 00:38:22.055
I HAD NO IDEA WE WERE
GETTING INTO THIS.


781
00:38:26.059 --> 00:38:29.018
Radio: A VIOLENT STORM
IS BATTERING THE NORTHERN
CALIFORNIA COAST.


782
00:38:29.062 --> 00:38:33.109
TV 8 HAS JUST RECEIVED WORD
THAT WINDS UP TO

783
00:38:33.153 --> 00:38:35.111
AND WAVES
CRESTING AT 30 FEET


784
00:38:35.155 --> 00:38:39.246
ARE CAUSING WIDESPREAD
