00:45:04.674 --> 00:45:06.285
NO! DON'T SAY THAT.

931
00:45:06.328 --> 00:45:07.590
JASON!

932
00:45:07.634 --> 00:45:09.984
JASON!

933
00:45:13.945 --> 00:45:15.250
Susan: JASON!

934
00:45:15.294 --> 00:45:17.296
JASON!

935
00:45:18.863 --> 00:45:21.213
Rick: JASON!

936
00:45:21.256 --> 00:45:23.041
PLEASE, WHERE ARE YOU?

937
00:45:23.084 --> 00:45:24.433
[GASPING]

938
00:45:24.477 --> 00:45:25.434
THERE HE IS!

939
00:45:25.478 --> 00:45:27.828
JASON, OVER HERE!

940
00:45:27.872 --> 00:45:29.787
SWIM FOR IT!

941
00:45:29.830 --> 00:45:31.614
GRAB IT!

942
00:45:31.658 --> 00:45:33.660
GRAB THE LINE!
HOLD ON!


943
00:45:33.703 --> 00:45:35.357
PULL, PULL. HELP ME.

944
00:45:35.401 --> 00:45:37.272
HANG ON!

945
00:45:37.316 --> 00:45:41.059
JASON, PLEASE!
HOLD ON!


946
00:45:41.102 --> 00:45:42.277
HOLD ON!

947
00:45:42.321 --> 00:45:43.975
OK, COME ON.

948
00:45:45.890 --> 00:45:47.326
PULL! PULL!

949
00:45:52.505 --> 00:45:53.593
PULL!

950
00:45:54.637 --> 00:45:56.422
WE GOT YA!
COME ON!


951
00:45:56.465 --> 00:45:58.598
COME ON!
COME ON. YEAH!


952
00:46:17.051 --> 00:46:19.358
HEY, HOW YA DOING?

953
00:46:19.401 --> 00:46:21.055
I'M OK.

954
00:46:21.099 --> 00:46:22.883
IS JASON ALL RIGHT?

955
00:46:22.927 --> 00:46:24.319
YEAH. HE'S FINE.

956
00:46:24.363 --> 00:46:26.887
LOOKS LIKE IT HURTS.

957
00:46:26.931 --> 00:46:27.888
UHH...

958
00:46:27.932 --> 00:46:29.890
ONLY WHEN THE BOAT MOVES.

959
00:46:31.936 --> 00:46:34.764
HERE. THIS SHOULD
CUSHION THE BUMPS.


960
00:46:34.808 --> 00:46:37.463
THANKS.

961
00:46:37.506 --> 00:46:40.422
SO HOW ARE YOU GUYS
DOING UP THERE?


962
00:46:40.466 --> 00:46:41.467
IT'S TOUGH,

963
00:46:41.510 --> 00:46:44.078
BUT WE'RE
HANGING IN THERE.


964
00:46:45.601 --> 00:46:47.255
IT'S BAD, ISN'T IT?

965
00:46:47.299 --> 00:46:50.563
"SEA-BROOK"
CAN HANDLE IT.


966
00:46:52.086 --> 00:46:53.566
YEAH, BUT CAN RICK?

967
00:46:58.963 --> 00:47:01.748
I GUESS I REALLY
DON'T KNOW WHAT KIND
OF CAPTAIN HE IS.


968
00:47:01.791 --> 00:47:03.837
HE'S DOING FINE.
DON'T WORRY.


969
00:47:17.416 --> 00:47:21.986
ALL THIS POUNDING,
IT FEELS LIKE WE'RE
JUST FALLING APART.


970
00:47:22.029 --> 00:47:23.509
I'M GONNA
GO BACK UP, OK?


971
00:47:34.476 --> 00:47:38.306
"SEA-BROOK," "SEA-BROOK,"
REQUEST TO KNOW
YOUR SITUATION. OVER.


972
00:47:38.350 --> 00:47:39.655
UH, ROGER, COAST GUARD.

973
00:47:39.699 --> 00:47:41.048
THIS IS "SEA
-BROOK."

974
00:47:41.092 --> 00:47:44.225
UM... MY RADAR SHOWS
THE STORM MOVING WEST.


975
00:47:44.269 --> 00:47:47.228
I THINK
WE'RE GONNA BE OK.


976
00:47:47.272 --> 00:47:48.882
SEAS ARE
PRETTY ROUGH OUT HERE,


977
00:47:48.926 --> 00:47:50.318
BUT I THINK WE'RE
GONNA MAKE IT.


978
00:47:50.362 --> 00:47:52.277
WE'RE HEADING INTO
SAN SIMEON. OVER.


979
00:47:52.320 --> 00:47:53.539
ROGER, "SEA
-BROOK."

980
00:47:53.582 --> 00:47:54.670
GLAD TO KNOW
YOU'RE OK.


981
00:47:54.714 --> 00:47:55.802
COAST GUARD OUT.

982
00:47:55.845 --> 00:47:57.804
ROGER. "SEA
-BROOK" OUT.

983
00:47:57.847 --> 00:47:59.980
WILL YOU
FILE THAT REPORT?


984
00:48:00.024 --> 00:48:02.069
COME ON, BABY.

985
00:48:06.682 --> 00:48:09.772
OH... SHEE...

986
00:48:09.816 --> 00:48:11.731
MAN, THE OWNER'S
GONNA HAVE RICK'S HIDE.


987
00:48:11.774 --> 00:48:14.081
WELL, AT LEAST SHE'S
STILL FLOATING.


988
00:48:14.125 --> 00:48:16.823
JASON...

989
00:48:16.866 --> 00:48:18.433
I WAS SO SCARED
WHEN...


990
00:48:18.477 --> 00:48:21.262
I KNOW.

991
00:48:21.306 --> 00:48:22.394
THANK YOU.

992
00:48:22.437 --> 00:48:23.656
[BEEEEEP]

993
00:48:23.699 --> 00:48:25.571
NO. NO, NOT AGAIN!

994
00:48:25.614 --> 00:48:27.007
OH, MAN.

995
00:48:27.051 --> 00:48:30.097
CHECK THE ENGINE, RICK.
CHECK THE ENGINE!


996
00:48:32.230 --> 00:48:33.883
WE NEED MORE SAIL.

997
00:48:33.927 --> 00:48:35.842
OK. I'LL GO LET HER OUT.
CAN YOU HOLD HER?


998
00:48:35.885 --> 00:48:36.974
YUP.

999
00:48:42.892 --> 00:48:44.459
CAREFUL, SUSAN.

1000
00:48:51.075 --> 00:48:52.293
EASE HER OUT SLOW.

1001
00:48:52.337 --> 00:48:53.164
I'M TRYING.

1002
00:48:56.471 --> 00:48:57.690
SLOWLY...

1003
00:48:57.733 --> 00:48:59.126
I CAN'T CLEAR IT.

1004
00:49:10.572 --> 00:49:12.444
AAH!

1005
00:49:12.487 --> 00:49:14.402
JASON! HELP ME!

1006
00:49:14.446 --> 00:49:15.534
SUSAN!

1007
00:49:18.058 --> 00:49:19.929
JASON!

1008
00:49:19.973 --> 00:49:21.670
ALL RIGHT. HOLD ON.
HOLD ON.


1009
00:49:21.714 --> 00:49:23.585
I GOT YOU.
ALL RIGHT,
DON'T LET GO.


1010
00:49:23.629 --> 00:49:25.500
PICK YOUR FEET UP.

1011
00:49:25.544 --> 00:49:26.719
I CAN'T.

1012
00:49:26.762 --> 00:49:29.026
YOU CAN. COME ON.
THERE YOU GO.


1013
00:49:29.069 --> 00:49:31.158
COME ON,
IT'S ALL RIGHT.
I GOT YOU.


1014
00:49:31.202 --> 00:49:33.204
I GOT YOU.
HANG ON TO ME.


1015
00:49:33.247 --> 00:49:35.467
GET UP. OK.

1016
00:49:35.510 --> 00:49:36.598
ALL RIGHT.

1017
00:49:39.340 --> 00:49:40.298
I'M OK.

1018
00:49:40.341 --> 00:49:42.126
I'LL FINISH
LOADING UP THE MAIN.


1019
00:49:42.169 --> 00:49:44.780
NO, NO. NO, FORGET IT.
THE STORM'S TOO BIG.


1020
00:49:44.824 --> 00:49:49.089
IF WE CAN'T FIX THE ENGINE,
WE GOTTA CALL FOR HELP.


1021
00:50:01.101 --> 00:50:02.059
YOU ALL RIGHT?

1022
00:50:02.102 --> 00:50:03.060
YEAH.

1023
00:50:03.103 --> 00:50:04.061
HUH? YOU OK?

1024
00:50:04.104 --> 00:50:05.149
YEAH.

1025
00:50:14.332 --> 00:50:15.724
RICK, WHAT
ARE YOU DOING?


1026
00:50:15.768 --> 00:50:18.901
YOU'RE SUPPOSED
TO BE FIXING THE
ENGINE, REMEMBER?


1027
00:50:18.945 --> 00:50:20.642
COULD YOU FIX
THE MAINSAIL?


1028
00:50:20.686 --> 00:50:22.122
I COULDN'T FREE IT.

1029
00:50:24.298 --> 00:50:26.257
THAT SEALS IT.
WE'RE DONE FOR.


1030
00:50:26.300 --> 00:50:28.128
RICK, WHAT ABOUT
THE ENGINE?


1031
00:50:28.172 --> 00:50:31.262
FORGET IT.
WE'RE SCREWED.


1032
00:50:31.305 --> 00:50:33.612
RICK, GET OFF YOUR ASS
AND START ACTING
LIKE A CAPTAIN.


1033
00:50:33.655 --> 00:50:36.397
RADIO THE COAST GUARD
FOR HELP.


1034
00:50:36.441 --> 00:50:38.138
THE STORM,
I THINK IT'S
MOVING WEST.


1035
00:50:38.182 --> 00:50:39.922
THE HELL IT IS.
WE'RE RIGHT IN
THE MIDDLE OF IT.


1036
00:50:39.966 --> 00:50:43.012
IF I CALL
THE COAST GUARD...


1037
00:50:43.056 --> 00:50:44.797
I'LL NEVER WORK
AGAIN.


1038
00:50:44.840 --> 00:50:46.233
WHAT?

1039
00:50:46.277 --> 00:50:48.366
YOU'RE SITTING HERE
THINKING ABOUT
YOUR CAREER?


1040
00:50:48.409 --> 00:50:50.716
RICK, WE'RE IN TROUBLE,
BIG TROUBLE.


1041
00:50:50.759 --> 00:50:52.021
WE'VE GOT TO CALL
THE COAST GUARD


1042
00:50:52.065 --> 00:50:54.807
AND PRAY WE CAN HOLD ON
TILL THEY GET HERE.


1043
00:50:54.850 --> 00:50:56.200
WHAT WAS THE NAME
OF THE VESSEL, MA'AM?


1044
00:50:56.243 --> 00:50:57.157
THE "SEA
-BROOK."

1045
00:50:57.201 --> 00:50:58.376
IT'S SAILING
UP TO VANCOUVER.


1046
00:50:58.419 --> 00:51:00.117
I'M AFRAID
IT MAY BE CAUGHT
IN THIS STORM.


1047
00:51:00.160 --> 00:51:02.510
UH, MA'AM, WE ARE
VERY BUSY RIGHT NOW.


1048
00:51:02.554 --> 00:51:04.164
BUT I'LL SEE IF I CAN
RAISE THEM ON THE RADIO.


1049
00:51:04.208 --> 00:51:05.818
CALL US BACK
IN AN HOUR, OK?


1050
00:51:05.861 --> 00:51:07.559
PLEASE. IT'S...
IT'S MY DAUGHTER.


1051
00:51:07.602 --> 00:51:09.952
WE'RE GONNA
DO OUR BEST.
I PROMISE.


1052
00:51:16.524 --> 00:51:19.092
LIEUTENANT,
I JUST SAW A REPORT
ON THE "SEA-BROOK."


1053
00:51:19.136 --> 00:51:20.615
IT SEEMS
THEY CALLED IN


1054
00:51:20.659 --> 00:51:22.574
AND SAID THEY WERE
SAFELY EN ROUTE
TO SAN SIMEON.


1055
00:51:22.617 --> 00:51:23.966
GOOD.

1056
00:51:30.712 --> 00:51:31.626
COAST GUARD?

1057
00:51:33.585 --> 00:51:34.934
COAST GUARD,
COME IN.


1058
00:51:34.977 --> 00:51:37.328
RICK, I CANNOT
HOLD HER ALONE!


1059
00:51:38.633 --> 00:51:41.114
AAH!

1060
00:51:41.158 --> 00:51:43.725
OH, MY GOD.

1061
00:51:43.769 --> 00:51:45.336
JASON,
START THE PUMPS!


1062
00:51:45.379 --> 00:51:47.512
I CAN'T GET UP!

1063
00:51:47.555 --> 00:51:49.775
MATT! MATT,
WE NEED YOU!


1064
00:51:49.818 --> 00:51:50.732
HELP ALLIE.

1065
00:51:50.776 --> 00:51:52.517
I'M GETTING
THE LIFE RAFT.


1066
00:51:52.560 --> 00:51:54.345
COME ON,
WE GOTTA GO!


1067
00:51:54.388 --> 00:51:55.607
AAH!

1068
00:51:55.650 --> 00:51:59.524
THERE'S NO POWER.
THE PUMPS
WON'T WORK.


1069
00:51:59.567 --> 00:52:01.743
MAYDAY! MAYDAY!

1070
00:52:04.833 --> 00:52:06.574
IT HURTS TO WALK!

1071
00:52:06.618 --> 00:52:09.664
I'M POPPING THE RAFT.
ABANDON SHIP!


1072
00:52:09.708 --> 00:52:11.275
WE'RE SINKING!
MAYDAY!


1073
00:52:12.406 --> 00:52:15.235
STAY RIGHT HERE.
I GOTTA LAUNCH
THE ZODIAC.


1074
00:52:24.810 --> 00:52:27.073
AAH! NO!!

1075
00:52:27.116 --> 00:52:28.553
UH...

1076
00:52:28.596 --> 00:52:29.423
UH...

1077
00:52:31.033 --> 00:52:33.862
JASON, LET'S
GET OUTTA HERE!
WE'RE GOIN' DOWN!


1078
00:52:38.867 --> 00:52:39.825
AAH!

1079
00:52:39.868 --> 00:52:41.305
AAH!

1080
00:52:48.573 --> 00:52:50.096
AAH!

1081
00:52:53.186 --> 00:52:55.057
HELP!

1082
00:52:55.101 --> 00:52:56.972
SOMEBODY HELP ME!

1083
00:53:01.063 --> 00:53:02.587
AAH!

1084
00:53:07.679 --> 00:53:09.724
IT'S OK, ALLIE.

1085
00:53:09.768 --> 00:53:10.725
HOLD ON...

1086
00:53:10.769 --> 00:53:11.857
HOLD ON.

1087
00:53:25.653 --> 00:53:27.264
OK, YOU'RE FREE.

1088
00:53:27.307 --> 00:53:29.266
SWIM AWAY FROM
THE BOAT. HURRY!


1089
00:53:49.721 --> 00:53:52.463
JASON!

1090
00:53:54.247 --> 00:53:55.292
ALLIE!

1091
00:54:05.824 --> 00:54:07.826
JASON!

1092
00:54:07.869 --> 00:54:10.176
SUSAN, OVER HERE!

1093
00:54:15.007 --> 00:54:16.748
OVER HERE!

1094
00:54:24.669 --> 00:54:26.105
WHERE'S ALLIE
AND JASON?


1095
00:54:26.148 --> 00:54:27.236
I DON'T KNOW.

1096
00:54:27.280 --> 00:54:28.977
ALLIE!

1097
00:54:29.021 --> 00:54:30.588
JASON!

1098
00:54:30.631 --> 00:54:31.980
ALLIE!

1099
00:54:32.024 --> 00:54:33.504
JASON!

1100
00:54:34.896 --> 00:54:38.378
RICK... RICK!

1101
00:54:38.422 --> 00:54:41.468
OVER HERE, MATT!
OVER HERE!


1102
00:54:41.512 --> 00:54:43.427
OVER HERE!

1103
00:54:45.080 --> 00:54:46.865
OVER HERE, MATT!

1104
00:54:46.908 --> 00:54:50.390
RICK! OHH...

1105
00:54:50.434 --> 00:54:51.783
YOU OK, BABY?

1106
00:54:51.826 --> 00:54:53.350
MY LEGS HURT.

1107
00:54:53.393 --> 00:54:54.438
HOLD ON!

1108
00:55:00.139 --> 00:55:01.445
WHERE'S JASON?

1109
00:55:01.488 --> 00:55:02.750
I DON'T KNOW.

1110
00:55:02.794 --> 00:55:04.099
WHAT HAPPENED
TO THE OTHER RAFT?


1111
00:55:04.143 --> 00:55:05.797
I COULDN'T
HOLD ON TO IT.


1112
00:55:05.840 --> 00:55:07.102
JASON!

1113
00:55:07.146 --> 00:55:08.408
WHAT DO YOU MEAN,
YOU COULDN'T HOLD
ON TO IT?


1114
00:55:08.452 --> 00:55:10.845
THAT HAD ALL OUR
EMERGENCY SUPPLIES.


1115
00:55:10.889 --> 00:55:12.499
WE'RE IN THE MIDDLE OF
A STORM HERE, REMEMBER?


1116
00:55:12.543 --> 00:55:13.979
WE'RE DEAD
WITHOUT THAT STUFF.


1117
00:55:14.022 --> 00:55:15.241
STOP IT!

1118
00:55:15.284 --> 00:55:17.635
IT'S OVER!
IT'S ALL OVER!


1119
00:55:17.678 --> 00:55:19.376
SHUT UP, RICK!
SHUT UP!


1120
00:55:19.419 --> 00:55:20.725
JASON!

1121
00:55:20.768 --> 00:55:21.900
I CAN'T HOLD ON.

1122
00:55:21.943 --> 00:55:24.337
HOLD ON, BABY.
JUST HOLD ON.


1123
00:55:24.381 --> 00:55:26.861
LET'S FLIP THE ZODIAC
AND GET IN.


1124
00:55:26.905 --> 00:55:30.038
OK. WE'LL
TAKE THE BACK.
YOU TAKE THE BOW.


1125
00:55:30.082 --> 00:55:32.563
ALL RIGHT.
THAT'S A GOOD IDEA.


1126
00:55:34.913 --> 00:55:36.349
OK, YOU READY?

1127
00:55:36.393 --> 00:55:38.438
HOLD ON, BABY.
HOLD ON.


1128
00:55:38.482 --> 00:55:41.746
1... 2...

1129
00:55:41.789 --> 00:55:42.877
3!

1130
00:55:44.531 --> 00:55:46.751
[SCREAMING]

1131
00:55:52.496 --> 00:55:54.454
COME ON, BABY, SWIM!

1132
00:55:54.498 --> 00:55:55.455
I CAN'T...

1133
00:55:55.499 --> 00:55:56.804
YOU CAN DO IT!

1134
00:56:10.296 --> 00:56:11.645
JASON, THANK GOD!

1135
00:56:11.689 --> 00:56:13.386
I GOT CAUGHT.

1136
00:56:13.430 --> 00:56:15.170
I GOT
DRAGGED UNDER.


1137
00:56:15.214 --> 00:56:18.609
OK, WE GOT TO
FLIP THIS AND GET IN.


1138
00:56:18.652 --> 00:56:20.611
IT'LL BLOW AWAY AGAIN!

1139
00:56:20.654 --> 00:56:22.395
WE'LL GRAB THE LINE
OVER THE LEEWARD SIDE


1140
00:56:22.439 --> 00:56:24.353
AND LET THE WIND
TURN IT OVER.


1141
00:56:24.397 --> 00:56:25.485
ALL RIGHT,
LET'S DO IT.


1142
00:56:25.529 --> 00:56:29.228
GO! GO!
OUT OF THE WAY!


1143
00:56:29.271 --> 00:56:32.579
GO TO THE
OTHER SIDE, ALLIE!


1144
00:56:39.020 --> 00:56:40.805
GET READY TO PULL!

1145
00:56:40.848 --> 00:56:44.199
OK. I'M READY.
GO AHEAD.


1146
00:56:44.243 --> 00:56:46.114
ALL RIGHT... AAH!

1147
00:56:53.165 --> 00:56:54.645
GIVE ME YOUR HAND!

1148
00:56:54.688 --> 00:56:56.124
HERE!

1149
00:56:56.168 --> 00:56:57.343
GIVE ME IT!

1150
00:57:12.706 --> 00:57:15.143
OH, MY GOD...
YOUR LEGS.


1151
00:57:15.187 --> 00:57:16.841
IT WAS THE RIGGING.

1152
00:57:16.884 --> 00:57:19.278
THIS WIND
IS SO COLD.


1153
00:57:19.321 --> 00:57:20.888
IT'S KILLING ME.

1154
00:57:20.932 --> 00:57:23.151
I'M TELLING YOU,
WE'RE BETTER OFF
IN THE WATER.


1155
00:57:23.195 --> 00:57:24.544
HE'S RIGHT.
WE SHOULD
GET BACK IN.


1156
00:57:24.588 --> 00:57:25.893
NO!

1157
00:57:25.937 --> 00:57:27.460
I CAN'T.

1158
00:57:27.504 --> 00:57:29.984
MAYBE IF WE BUNCH UP...
CONSERVE BODY HEAT.


1159
00:57:30.028 --> 00:57:31.943
Rick: IT'S TOO
COLD OUT HERE.


1160
00:57:31.986 --> 00:57:33.727
PLEASE DON'T MAKE ME
GET BACK IN.


1161
00:57:33.771 --> 00:57:34.728
OK. WE WON'T.

1162
00:57:34.772 --> 00:57:36.121
LET'S JUST STAY CLOSE.

1163
00:57:39.298 --> 00:57:40.560
IT'S OVER.

1164
00:57:40.604 --> 00:57:42.040
I JUST
KNOW IT'S OVER.


1165
00:57:42.083 --> 00:57:43.171
OH, SHUT UP!

1166
00:57:43.215 --> 00:57:44.956
COME ON, GUYS, WE
HAVE TO WORK TOGETHER.


1167
00:57:44.999 --> 00:57:47.262
IT'S OUR ONLY HOPE
UNTIL WE GET RESCUED.


1168
00:57:47.306 --> 00:57:50.222
SOMEBODY MUST HAVE
HEARD YOUR MAYDAY.


1169
00:57:50.265 --> 00:57:51.832
THEY'RE NOT COMING.

1170
00:57:51.876 --> 00:57:52.833
STOP SAYING THAT!

1171
00:57:52.877 --> 00:57:54.356
NO, I MEAN,
THEY'RE NOT COMING.


1172
00:57:54.400 --> 00:57:56.141
I TOLD THEM
NOT TO COME.


1173
00:57:56.184 --> 00:57:57.708
WHAT?
WHAT?


1174
00:57:57.751 --> 00:58:00.537
I SAW YOU TALKING...
I MEAN, BEFORE THE
BOAT WENT DOWN.


1175
00:58:00.580 --> 00:58:02.626
I TRIED. IT WAS
WATERLOGGED BY THEN.


1176
00:58:02.669 --> 00:58:04.062
DAMN!

1177
00:58:04.105 --> 00:58:06.194
WE ARE GONNA DIE.

1178
00:58:06.238 --> 00:58:08.806
NO. WE'RE GONNA SURVIVE.

1179
00:58:08.849 --> 00:58:10.416
IN THE MORNING THEY'LL
BE LOOKING FOR US.


1180
00:58:10.459 --> 00:58:11.765
WE CAN CERTAINLY
HOLD OUT TILL THEN.


1181
00:58:11.809 --> 00:58:13.419
THERE ARE SHARKS
ALL THROUGH THESE WATERS.


1182
00:58:13.462 --> 00:58:14.507
THERE'S GREAT WHITES.

1183
00:58:14.551 --> 00:58:17.336
BUT WE SHOULD BE
SAFE IN HERE.


1184
00:58:22.863 --> 00:58:24.604
THIS IS MY FAULT.

1185
00:58:26.867 --> 00:58:28.652
THIS IS ALL MY FAULT.

1186
00:58:45.451 --> 00:58:47.453
Susan: WHEN DAY
FINALLY BROKE,


1187
00:58:47.496 --> 00:58:49.629
WHAT I SAW SCARED ME.

1188
00:58:49.673 --> 00:58:51.979
OF COURSE, OUR BOAT
WAS LONG GONE...


1189
00:58:52.023 --> 00:58:55.504
RESTING QUIETLY
ON THE BOTTOM OF
THE PACIFIC OCEAN.


1190
00:58:55.548 --> 00:58:57.419
PLUS WE HAD NO SUPPLIES...

1191
00:58:57.463 --> 00:59:00.814
NO FOOD, NO WATER,
AND NO CAPTAIN.


1192
00:59:00.858 --> 00:59:03.382
AS RICK HAD LOST ALL HOPE,

1193
00:59:03.425 --> 00:59:06.777
HE HAD NOTHING TO OFFER
IN TERMS OF LEADERSHIP.


1194
00:59:06.820 --> 00:59:09.954
ALLIE WAS IN TERRIBLE PAIN,
TRYING HARD TO BE RONG,


1195
00:59:09.997 --> 00:59:12.521
AND MATT WAS EDGY
AND QUICK-TEMPERED.


1196
00:59:12.565 --> 00:59:16.569
IT WAS UP TO ME AND JASON
TO KEEP EVERYONE'S
SPIRITS UP.


1197
00:59:16.613 --> 00:59:17.788
I WAS SCARED AS HELL.

1198
00:59:17.831 --> 00:59:18.832
WE NEED A COVER.

1199
00:59:18.876 --> 00:59:20.660
JASON...

1200
00:59:20.704 --> 00:59:23.489
DO WE HAVE ANYTHING
TO MAKE A CANOPY?


1201
00:59:23.532 --> 00:59:24.621
UM...

1202
00:59:28.233 --> 00:59:29.713
YEAH. UM...

1203
00:59:39.548 --> 00:59:40.767
THIS WILL WORK.

1204
00:59:40.811 --> 00:59:42.377
LET'S SET IT UP,

1205
00:59:42.421 --> 00:59:44.031
AND THEN WE CAN TAKE
TURNS KEEPING WATCH


1206
00:59:44.075 --> 00:59:45.598
UNTIL A SHIP COMES.

1207
00:59:48.906 --> 00:59:49.863
HEY...

1208
00:59:49.907 --> 00:59:50.951
GET UP, GUYS.

1209
00:59:50.995 --> 00:59:51.996
HELP US OU

1210
00:59:52.039 --> 00:59:53.519
WE'RE GONNA MAKE A CANOPY.

1211
01:01:05.547 --> 01:01:06.853
WHAT ARE YOU DOING?

1212
01:01:06.897 --> 01:01:10.030
STOP. DON'T DRINK THAT.
IT'LL MAKE YOU CRAZY.


1213
01:01:10.074 --> 01:01:12.076
A SMALL AMOUNT
WON'T HURT.


1214
01:01:12.119 --> 01:01:14.121
YOU'RE BETTER OFF
DRINKING YOUR
OWN URINE.


1215
01:01:14.165 --> 01:01:17.690
YOU DRINK WHAT YOU WANT,
I'LL DRINK WHAT I WANT.


1216
01:01:17.734 --> 01:01:20.475
HERE YOU GO, BABY.
HAVE A LITTLE WATER.


1217
01:01:20.519 --> 01:01:21.433
NO!

1218
01:01:21.476 --> 01:01:22.651
DAMN IT!
YOU LITTLE...


1219
01:01:22.695 --> 01:01:23.914
AAH!

1220
01:01:23.957 --> 01:01:24.915
STAY AWAY!

1221
01:01:24.958 --> 01:01:26.481
AAH! GET OFF!

1222
01:01:26.525 --> 01:01:28.266
HEY, WHAT ARE
YOU DOING?!


1223
01:01:28.309 --> 01:01:30.137
OH, MAN!

1224
01:01:32.749 --> 01:01:34.402
IT'S OK.

1225
01:01:34.446 --> 01:01:36.840
IT'S OK.
I'M FINE.


1226
01:01:36.883 --> 01:01:39.799
IT'S JUST MY LEG
HURTS SO BAD. [SOBS]


1227
01:01:41.322 --> 01:01:42.628
IT'S OK.

1228
01:01:45.152 --> 01:01:45.979
IT'S OK, BABY.

1229
01:01:51.506 --> 01:01:53.639
OH...

1230
01:01:53.682 --> 01:01:57.861
OH...
WHAT HAVE I DONE TO
MY BEAUTIFUL BABY?


1231
01:01:57.904 --> 01:01:59.384
WHAT HAVE I DONE?

1232
01:02:02.082 --> 01:02:03.780
I'VE RUINED
EVERYTHING.


1233
01:02:11.918 --> 01:02:13.920
AT LEAST THE STORM PASSED.

1234
01:02:20.274 --> 01:02:22.581
HERE COMES THE SUN.

1235
01:03:11.108 --> 01:03:13.980
I DON'T THINK I CAN STAND
ANOTHER NIGHT HERE.


1236
01:03:15.939 --> 01:03:18.245
THIS IS THE LAST
ONE, ALLIE.


1237
01:03:18.289 --> 01:03:20.900
WE'LL BE RESCUED
TOMORROW.


1238
01:03:20.944 --> 01:03:22.032
REALLY?

1239
01:03:22.075 --> 01:03:24.295
MM
-HMM.

1240
01:03:24.338 --> 01:03:28.038
RICK, DO YOU THINK SO?

1241
01:03:28.081 --> 01:03:31.476
WE DON'T NEED
TO BE RESCUED.


1242
01:03:31.519 --> 01:03:32.433
I SEE SHORE.

1243
01:03:32.477 --> 01:03:34.740
WHERE?

1244
01:03:34.783 --> 01:03:36.046
Rick:
OVER THERE.


1245
01:03:39.788 --> 01:03:41.355
WE'RE OFF
MISSION BAY.


1246
01:03:41.399 --> 01:03:43.053
WE'RE NOWHERE NEAR
MISSION BAY.


1247
01:03:43.096 --> 01:03:45.011
YES, WE ARE.
I RECOGNIZE
THE BUILDINGS.


1248
01:03:45.055 --> 01:03:46.752
ARE... ARE YOU SURE?

1249
01:03:46.795 --> 01:03:48.319
RICK, YOU'RE
SEEING THINGS.


1250
01:03:48.362 --> 01:03:51.104
YOU'VE BEEN DRINKING
TOO MUCH SEA WATER.
YOU'RE CONFUSED.


1251
01:03:51.148 --> 01:03:52.540
NO, NO, NO.
IT'S THERE.


1252
01:03:52.584 --> 01:03:54.716
COME ON, BUDDY,
SIT DOWN.


1253
01:03:54.760 --> 01:03:56.109
SIT DOWN.
SIT DOWN.


1254
01:03:56.153 --> 01:03:59.547
Allie: RICK...
WHAT ARE YOU DOING?


1255
01:03:59.591 --> 01:04:01.506
RICK, NO!
RICK!


1256
01:04:01.549 --> 01:04:02.507
RICK, NO!

1257
01:04:02.550 --> 01:04:04.857
COME BACK!

1258
01:04:04.901 --> 01:04:06.641
RICK, PLEASE,
DON'T LEAVE ME!


1259
01:04:06.685 --> 01:04:07.773
I GOTTA GO
AFTER HIM!


1260
01:04:07.816 --> 01:04:09.949
NO, NO!
IT'S PITCH DARK
OUT THERE.


1261
01:04:09.993 --> 01:04:13.126
YOU'D BOTH BE LOST.
IT'S SUICIDE.


1262
01:04:15.085 --> 01:04:16.129
I KNOW.

1263
01:04:19.306 --> 01:04:20.568
OH, MY GOD!

1264
01:04:25.704 --> 01:04:27.140
OH, MY GOD!

1265
01:04:54.907 --> 01:04:55.952
AAH!

1266
01:04:58.389 --> 01:04:59.216
OW!

1267
01:05:00.957 --> 01:05:03.263
COME ON, SUSAN, WAKE UP.
WAKE UP, WAKE UP, WAKE UP.


1268
01:05:03.307 --> 01:05:05.396
OH, I THINK
I'M LOSING IT.


1269
01:05:05.439 --> 01:05:06.788
NO, NO, YOU'RE NOT.

1270
01:05:06.832 --> 01:05:09.139
IT WAS JUST A BAD DREAM,
JUST A BAD DREAM.


1271
01:05:09.182 --> 01:05:12.925
OK. I'M OK NOW.

1272
01:05:12.969 --> 01:05:15.145
WE'RE ALL
JUST SO HUNGRY
AND THIRSTY.


1273
01:05:18.800 --> 01:05:21.499
IT'S OK TO LEAN ON ME
A LITTLE BIT, YOU KNOW.


1274
01:05:21.542 --> 01:05:24.328
NO, IT'S NOT.
WE HAVE TO BE STRONG.


1275
01:05:24.371 --> 01:05:27.635
YOU CAN'T BE EXPECTED
TO DO IT FOR BOTH OF US.


1276
01:05:29.028 --> 01:05:30.987
THIS IS NOT
A COMPETITION, SUSAN.


1277
01:05:33.554 --> 01:05:35.600
WHAT'S GOING ON?

1278
01:05:35.643 --> 01:05:37.254
NOTHING, ALLIE.
GO BACK TO SLEEP.


1279
01:05:42.781 --> 01:05:44.913
I'M JUST GONNA
COVER YOU UP, OK?


1280
01:05:44.957 --> 01:05:46.698
NO, I DON'T
WANNA WAKE UP.


1281
01:05:46.741 --> 01:05:47.829
SHH.

1282
01:05:49.440 --> 01:05:50.267
I DON'T.

1283
01:05:53.009 --> 01:05:55.707
I DON'T WANNA
REMEMBER...


1284
01:05:55.750 --> 01:05:57.578
OR FEEL THIS PAIN.

1285
01:06:00.320 --> 01:06:01.365
AND NOW RICK...

1286
01:06:07.980 --> 01:06:10.026
I DON'T THINK
HE MADE IT.


1287
01:06:14.073 --> 01:06:15.988
DO YOU THINK
HE MADE IT?


1288
01:06:16.032 --> 01:06:17.642
NO.

1289
01:06:20.514 --> 01:06:23.909
BUT WE'RE STILL HERE.
WE'RE GONNA LIVE
THROUGH THIS.


1290
01:06:26.303 --> 01:06:29.610
IT JUST SEEMS
SO MUCH EASIER
TO DIE NOW...


1291
01:06:29.654 --> 01:06:32.744
LIKE HE OPENED
THE DOOR.


1292
01:06:32.787 --> 01:06:34.659
RICK DIDN'T DIE.

1293
01:06:34.702 --> 01:06:36.617
ALLIE, HE KILLED
HIMSELF.


1294
01:06:40.708 --> 01:06:43.102
RICK GAVE UP WHEN
THE BOAT SANK, ALLIE.


1295
01:06:43.146 --> 01:06:45.409
AFTER THAT, ALL HE
CARED ABOUT WAS YOU.


1296
01:06:52.155 --> 01:06:56.246
I... I DON'T WANNA DIE.

1297
01:06:56.289 --> 01:06:58.117
[SNIFFLING]

1298
01:07:01.077 --> 01:07:03.775
PLEASE DON'T LET ME
GIVE UP.


1299
01:07:03.818 --> 01:07:05.646
I WON'T.

1300
01:07:14.002 --> 01:07:16.657
[TRAIN WHISTLE BLOWING]

1301
01:07:23.011 --> 01:07:24.752
DON'T TELL ME TO WAIT.

1302
01:07:24.796 --> 01:07:26.711
MY DAUGHTER COULD
BE LOST OUT THERE.


1303
01:07:26.754 --> 01:07:28.495
LISTEN, I UNDERSTAND
YOUR CONCERN,


1304
01:07:28.539 --> 01:07:30.932
BUT WE HAVE NO EVIDENCE
OF ANY TROUBLE.


1305
01:07:30.976 --> 01:07:33.283
NOW, LAST WE HEARD,
THEY WERE HEADED NORTH.


1306
01:07:33.326 --> 01:07:35.241
AND I AM TELLING
YOU, I KNOW
MY DAUGHTER.


1307
01:07:35.285 --> 01:07:37.939
I WANT TO TALK
TO THE OFFICER
IN CHARGE.


1308
01:07:37.983 --> 01:07:39.941
HE WILL BE HERE AS SOON
AS HE POSSIBLY CAN...


1309
01:07:39.985 --> 01:07:40.942
I'M LIEUTENANT BELWICK,
MA'AM.


1310
01:07:40.986 --> 01:07:42.292
WHAT SEEMS TO BE
THE PROBLEM?


1311
01:07:42.335 --> 01:07:44.120
THE TROUBLE IS
MY DAUGHTER'S BOAT
IS MISSING.


1312
01:07:44.163 --> 01:07:45.469
EVERYBODY KEEPS
SAYING HER BOAT
IS SAFE,


1313
01:07:45.512 --> 01:07:47.123
BUT NOBODY
SEEMS TO KNOW
WHERE IT IS.


1314
01:07:47.166 --> 01:07:48.211
YOU MUST BE
MRS. CLARKSON,


1315
01:07:48.254 --> 01:07:50.561
AND YES,
LAST WE HEARD,
"SEA-BROOK"


1316
01:07:50.604 --> 01:07:52.693
WAS SAFELY
ON ITS WAY TO DOCK
IN SAN SIMEON.


1317
01:07:52.737 --> 01:07:55.305
IT NEVER ARRIVED.
SHE WOULD'VE
CALLED ME.


1318
01:07:55.348 --> 01:07:58.221
I UNDERSTAND, BUT MAYBE
SHE JUST FORGOT DURING
ALL THE CONFUSION.


1319
01:07:58.264 --> 01:07:59.570
SHE DIDN'T FORGET.

1320
01:08:02.268 --> 01:08:03.835
SOMETHING IS WRONG.

1321
01:08:03.878 --> 01:08:06.098
MY DAUGHTER IS IN
TROUBLE OUT THERE,


1322
01:08:06.142 --> 01:08:09.101
AND I AM NOT GOING
TO RISK HER LIFE


1323
01:08:09.145 --> 01:08:12.539
BECAUSE
YOU'RE SATISFIED
THAT SHE'S SAFE.


1324
01:08:13.801 --> 01:08:15.238
PLEASE, COME IN.

1325
01:09:19.954 --> 01:09:22.305
WHERE ARE MY CIGARETTES?
THEY WERE RIGHT HERE.


1326
01:09:24.089 --> 01:09:25.917
WHAT ARE YOU
TALKING ABOUT?


1327
01:09:25.960 --> 01:09:28.224
MY DAMN CIGARETTES.
WHO TOOK 'EM?


1328
01:09:29.529 --> 01:09:31.749
OK, GUYS,
I WANT MY CIGARETTES
BACK RIGHT NOW.


1329
01:09:31.792 --> 01:09:32.924
THEY WERE RIGHT HERE.

1330
01:09:32.967 --> 01:09:34.491
MATT, THEY SANK
WITH THE BOAT,
REMEMBER?


1331
01:09:34.534 --> 01:09:36.101
NO. I'M TALKING ABOUT
THE OTHER CIGARETTES.


1332
01:09:36.144 --> 01:09:37.276
WHAT OTHER CIGARETTES...

1333
01:09:37.320 --> 01:09:39.278
THE ONES I BOUGHT
AT THE STORE, MAN!


1334
01:09:39.322 --> 01:09:40.888
I BOUGHT BEER,
AND I BOUGHT...
MATT!


1335
01:09:40.932 --> 01:09:42.107
WHOA, MATT.

1336
01:09:42.150 --> 01:09:43.891
IF YOU WENT
TO THE STORE...


1337
01:09:43.935 --> 01:09:45.458
LOOK AT ME...

1338
01:09:45.502 --> 01:09:48.418
WHY DID YOU
COME BACK?


1339
01:10:34.377 --> 01:10:36.379
"SEA
-BROOK."

1340
01:10:36.422 --> 01:10:38.294
"SEA-BROOK,"
COME IN. OVER.


1341
01:10:40.078 --> 01:10:42.385
THE SKIES HAVE BEEN
CLEAR FOR 2 DAYS.


1342
01:10:42.428 --> 01:10:43.777
THEY SHOULD BE ANSWERING.

1343
01:10:43.821 --> 01:10:46.389
ALL RIGHT. LET'S
MARK THEIR LAST KNOWN
COORDINATES,


1344
01:10:46.432 --> 01:10:48.521
SEE IF ANY OTHER VESSELS
ARE IN THE AREA.


1345
01:10:48.565 --> 01:10:50.175
2-way radio:
ALL STATIONS,


1346
01:10:50.218 --> 01:10:52.786
THIS IS UNITED STATES
COAST GUARD,
LOS ANGELES GROUP.


1347
01:10:52.830 --> 01:10:55.006
BE ON THE LOOKOUT
FOR "SEA-BROOK,"


1348
01:10:55.049 --> 01:10:58.705
A 68-FOOT, BLUE-HULLED
SAILING VESSEL WITH

1349
01:10:58.749 --> 01:11:01.839
LAST REPORTED 16 MILES
SOUTHWEST OF MORRO BAY,
CALIFORNIA.


1350
01:11:16.636 --> 01:11:17.637
MATT, DON'T!

1351
01:11:17.681 --> 01:11:19.639
I'M THIRSTY!
YOU'LL KILL
YOURSELF.


1352
01:11:19.683 --> 01:11:21.337
YOU SAW WHAT
IT DID TO RICK.


1353
01:11:21.380 --> 01:11:23.295
LEAVE ME ALONE!
I'VE BEEN DRINKING
IT ALL DAY!


1354
01:11:23.339 --> 01:11:24.731
STOP IT!
HEY, HEY, HEY...


1355
01:11:24.775 --> 01:11:26.167
TELL HER TO SHUT UP!
IT'S NOT HER BUSINESS!


1356
01:11:26.211 --> 01:11:27.255
LEAVE HIM
ALONE, SUSAN.


1357
01:11:27.299 --> 01:11:28.692
WE CAN'T LET HIM
KILL HIMSELF!


1358
01:11:28.735 --> 01:11:30.911
YOU CAN'T MAKE
HIM SURVIVE IF HE
DOESN'T WANT TO.


1359
01:11:30.955 --> 01:11:33.349
FINE. LET HIM DIE.
I'M SICK OF FIGHTING
WITH HIM.


1360
01:11:36.569 --> 01:11:38.832
OH... SHEE...

1361
01:11:43.837 --> 01:11:45.665
LOOK AT THIS FILTH.

1362
01:11:47.450 --> 01:11:51.236
UGH... IT'S POISON,
MAN. LOOK AT IT.


1363
01:11:51.279 --> 01:11:53.107
UGH... UGH...

1364
01:11:53.151 --> 01:11:55.936
MATT.
WE'RE SITTING
IN POISON, MAN.


1365
01:11:55.980 --> 01:11:56.937
IT'S GONNA KILL US!

1366
01:11:56.981 --> 01:11:57.938
MATT...
NO, IT WON'T.


1367
01:11:57.982 --> 01:11:59.679
WE GOTTA GET
OUT OF HERE.


1368
01:11:59.723 --> 01:12:01.420
NO, MATT. HOW?
LISTEN...


1369
01:12:01.464 --> 01:12:02.813
WE GOTTA
DUMP IT OUT.


1370
01:12:02.856 --> 01:12:04.292
FLIP THE RAFT,
DUMP IT OUT.


1371
01:12:04.336 --> 01:12:05.511
THERE'S SHARKS
ALL OVER THE PLACE.


1372
01:12:05.555 --> 01:12:06.686
YOU GOTTA THINK
ABOUT THIS, OK?


1373
01:12:06.730 --> 01:12:08.558
GOD, IT'S
BURNING ME.


1374
01:12:08.601 --> 01:12:10.429
STOP IT, MATT.
ALLIE'S
TOO WEAK
TO SWIM.


1375
01:12:10.473 --> 01:12:11.865
TURN IT OVER NOW!

1376
01:12:11.909 --> 01:12:12.997
WE GOTTA EMPTY IT!

1377
01:12:13.040 --> 01:12:16.043
WHAT'S GOING ON?
ARE WE BEING RESCUED?


1378
01:12:16.087 --> 01:12:18.132
NO, BUT WE'RE DYING.
THIS WATER'S KILLING US.


1379
01:12:18.176 --> 01:12:19.177
MATT, NO!

1380
01:12:19.220 --> 01:12:20.352
NO, NO...

1381
01:12:20.396 --> 01:12:21.832
UH... AAH!

1382
01:12:26.227 --> 01:12:27.446
NO, JASON!

1383
01:12:32.669 --> 01:12:34.235
MATT, DAMN YOU!

1384
01:12:34.279 --> 01:12:35.411
COME ON IN!
IT'S PERFECT!


1385
01:12:39.371 --> 01:12:40.416
AH! SOMETHING
JUST BUMPED ME.


1386
01:12:40.459 --> 01:12:42.722
Susan: SHARKS!
JASON, HURRY, GET IN!


1387
01:12:42.766 --> 01:12:44.158
Jason:
KICK, ALLIE, KICK!


1388
01:12:44.202 --> 01:12:45.595
HURRY, JASON, GET IN!

1389
01:12:45.638 --> 01:12:46.987
MOVE YOUR LEGS!
MOVE YOUR LEGS!


1390
01:12:47.031 --> 01:12:48.206
COME ON,
HELP HER UP.


1391
01:12:48.249 --> 01:12:50.600
GRAB HER.
I GOT YOU, ALLIE.


1392
01:12:50.643 --> 01:12:52.036
Susan:
JASON!


1393
01:12:52.079 --> 01:12:54.038
MATT! NO, WHAT
ARE YOU DOING?


1394
01:12:54.081 --> 01:12:55.126
GET IN THE RAFT!

1395
01:12:55.169 --> 01:12:57.084
COME ON!

1396
01:12:57.128 --> 01:13:00.131
MATT, NO!

1397
01:13:00.174 --> 01:13:03.221
MATT... GRAB MY HAND!

1398
01:13:03.264 --> 01:13:04.222
HELP!

1399
01:13:04.265 --> 01:13:06.006
GET IN THE RAFT!

1400
01:13:08.226 --> 01:13:10.446
[GRUNTING]

1401
01:13:12.317 --> 01:13:14.275
AAH!

1402
01:13:14.319 --> 01:13:16.800
Jason:
MATT! MATT!


1403
01:13:16.843 --> 01:13:17.844
AAAAAH!

1404
01:13:17.888 --> 01:13:20.064
DON'T LOOK.

1405
01:13:20.107 --> 01:13:23.720
AAH! AAH! AAH!

1406
01:13:43.217 --> 01:13:45.611
[MOANING]

1407
01:13:54.533 --> 01:13:58.058
SHE'S PRETTY BAD.
I THINK IT'S
BLOOD POISONING.


1408
01:13:58.102 --> 01:13:59.625
WHAT SHOULD WE DO?

1409
01:14:02.889 --> 01:14:04.717
A TOURNIQUET
AROUND HER LEG


1410
01:14:04.761 --> 01:14:07.938
MIGHT HELP
STOP THE INFECTION
FROM SPREADING.


1411
01:14:07.981 --> 01:14:11.507
A TOURNIQUET.
UM...


1412
01:14:12.812 --> 01:14:14.945
WELL...

1413
01:14:14.988 --> 01:14:16.207
OH, HERE.

1414
01:14:18.209 --> 01:14:20.907
HERE, USE THIS BELT.

1415
01:14:20.951 --> 01:14:23.910
LISTEN, ALLIE,
I'M WORRIED ABOUT
YOUR LEG, OK?


1416
01:14:23.954 --> 01:14:27.000
WE'RE GONNA PUT
A TOURNIQUET ON
IT, ALL RIGHT?


1417
01:14:27.044 --> 01:14:28.175
TOURNIQUET?

1418
01:14:28.219 --> 01:14:29.220
TO HELP YOU.
WHY?


1419
01:14:29.263 --> 01:14:31.178
ALL RIGHT?
IT MIGHT HURT
A LITTLE...


1420
01:14:31.222 --> 01:14:32.745
BUT IT'LL STOP
THE INFECTION


1421
01:14:32.789 --> 01:14:33.790
FROM SPREADING,
OK?


1422
01:14:33.833 --> 01:14:35.095
OW!

1423
01:14:35.139 --> 01:14:37.750
ALL RIGHT. JUST
HOLD STILL FOR
ONE SECOND, OK?


1424
01:14:37.794 --> 01:14:39.317
WHAT ARE YOU...

1425
01:14:43.756 --> 01:14:46.542
[GASPS] OWW!
GUYS, GET AWAY
FROM ME!


1426
01:14:46.585 --> 01:14:47.586
ALL RIGHT,
ALL RIGHT!


1427
01:14:47.630 --> 01:14:49.719
STOP! GET OFF!

1428
01:14:49.762 --> 01:14:51.459
ALL RIGHT, ALL RIGHT!
IT'S OFF, IT'S OFF.


1429
01:14:51.503 --> 01:14:52.504
ALL RIGHT.

1430
01:14:52.548 --> 01:14:54.245
DON'T TOUCH ME.

1431
01:14:54.288 --> 01:14:56.377
IT'S OK,
IT'S OK,
IT'S OK.


1432
01:14:58.379 --> 01:15:00.512
[SOBBING]

1433
01:15:00.556 --> 01:15:04.516
IT'S ALL RIGHT.
IT'S OVER. IT'S
OK, IT'S OK.


1434
01:15:07.040 --> 01:15:10.478
I'M JUST GONNA PLAY IT
REAL STRAIGHT WITH YOU,
MRS. CLARKSON...


1435
01:15:10.522 --> 01:15:12.350
WE CANNOT FIND ANY EVIDENCE

1436
01:15:12.393 --> 01:15:16.223
THAT YOUR DAUGHTER'S BOAT
EVER REACHED SAN SIMEON.


1437
01:15:16.267 --> 01:15:17.790
AND, UH...

1438
01:15:17.834 --> 01:15:20.880
WHAT ARE YOU DOING
TO TRY TO FIND HER?


1439
01:15:20.924 --> 01:15:24.928
WE ARE CHECKING
EVERY HARBOR AND
MARINA UP THE COAST.


1440
01:15:24.971 --> 01:15:28.409
WE HAVE A WATCH ALERT
OUT TO ALL VESSELS
IN THE AREA.


1441
01:15:28.453 --> 01:15:30.237
UH, WHAT ABOUT
AIRPLANES,
HELICOPTERS?


1442
01:15:30.281 --> 01:15:32.022
WE'RE CONSIDERING
THAT, TOO.


1443
01:15:32.065 --> 01:15:33.806
CONSIDERING ISN'T
ENOUGH, DAMN IT!


1444
01:15:33.850 --> 01:15:36.766
YOU JUST GET
THE HELL OUT THERE
AND FIND HER!


1445
01:15:40.596 --> 01:15:43.903
2-way radio: POINT REYES,
THIS IS COAST GUARD 1503,


1446
01:15:43.947 --> 01:15:47.515
ON SCENE, COMMENCING
PAPA-SIERRA SEARCH
AT MINUTE 0-8.


1447
01:15:47.559 --> 01:15:50.518
MAJOR AXIS IS

1448
01:15:50.562 --> 01:15:53.260
TRACKING SPACE
IS 5 MILES...


1449
01:16:11.365 --> 01:16:16.370
AH... AHH... OHH...

1450
01:16:16.414 --> 01:16:18.982
SO HOT.
THERE'S NO BREEZE.
THERE'S NO NOTHING.


1451
01:16:19.025 --> 01:16:21.375
LET'S GET IN THE WATER
AND COOL OFF.


1452
01:16:21.419 --> 01:16:23.247
COME ON, SUSAN,
COME ON. NO,
YOU CAN'T.


1453
01:16:23.290 --> 01:16:24.640
NO, I HAVE TO COOL OFF.

1454
01:16:24.683 --> 01:16:28.382
SUSAN, STOP IT.
COME ON, STOP. STOP!


1455
01:16:28.426 --> 01:16:30.994
WHAT... WHAT
ARE YOU DOING?


1456
01:16:31.037 --> 01:16:33.605
PLEASE, YOU CAN'T...
YOU CAN'T LEAVE ME HERE.


1457
01:16:33.649 --> 01:16:35.825
WE'RE NOT GOING
ANYWHERE, ALLIE.


1458
01:16:53.277 --> 01:16:55.453
LOOK... LOOK.

1459
01:17:09.859 --> 01:17:11.382
AH! HA HA!

1460
01:17:11.425 --> 01:17:13.427
I CAUGHT ONE!
I CAUGHT IT!


1461
01:17:13.471 --> 01:17:15.473
HA HA HA HA!

1462
01:17:15.516 --> 01:17:16.996
WHAT'S GOING ON?

1463
01:17:17.040 --> 01:17:19.869
WE CAUGHT A FISH.
WE GOT SOMETHING TO EAT.


1464
01:17:21.827 --> 01:17:24.047
HEH HEH.
OH... OH.


1465
01:17:27.528 --> 01:17:30.618
OK. ALL RIGHT.

1466
01:17:33.056 --> 01:17:34.579
THERE. HERE.

1467
01:17:34.622 --> 01:17:36.320
GIVE SOME
TO ALLIE, FIRST.


1468
01:17:36.363 --> 01:17:38.148
YEAH, YEAH.
HERE, ALLIE.
NO.


1469
01:17:38.191 --> 01:17:39.584
YEAH, COME ON.
IT'LL HELP.


1470
01:17:39.627 --> 01:17:41.281
PROTEIN
WILL FIGHT
THE INFECTION.


1471
01:17:41.325 --> 01:17:42.413
I CAN'T.

1472
01:17:42.456 --> 01:17:45.546
HERE. LET ME TRY.

1473
01:17:49.637 --> 01:17:51.465
COME ON, ALLIE,
JUST A BITE.


1474
01:18:04.783 --> 01:18:05.871
NO.

1475
01:18:09.440 --> 01:18:12.443
WHAT WAS THAT
BACK THERE?


1476
01:18:12.486 --> 01:18:15.185
I DON'T KNOW.
I JUST...


1477
01:18:15.228 --> 01:18:18.405
I WOKE UP AND I JUST
REMEMBERED WANTING
TO COOL OFF.


1478
01:18:18.449 --> 01:18:20.407
DON'T WORRY.
IT WON'T HAPPEN AGAIN.


1479
01:18:20.451 --> 01:18:22.366
YOU ARE DETERMINED

1480
01:18:22.409 --> 01:18:24.716
TO GO THROUGH THIS
ALONE, AREN'T YOU,
SUSAN?


1481
01:18:24.760 --> 01:18:26.283
NO, BUT I PULL
MY OWN WEIGHT...


1482
01:18:26.326 --> 01:18:29.765
DAMN IT, SUSAN.
HAVEN'T YOU SEEN
ENOUGH DYING


1483
01:18:29.808 --> 01:18:31.114
ON THIS RAFT?

1484
01:18:31.157 --> 01:18:33.681
WE NEED TO HELP
EACH OTHER, SUSAN.


1485
01:18:36.597 --> 01:18:38.121
DON'T YOU
UNDERSTAND...


1486
01:18:38.164 --> 01:18:42.081
THAT IT'S OK
TO NEED EACH OTHER?


1487
01:18:45.258 --> 01:18:46.216
I KNOW.

1488
01:18:53.789 --> 01:18:57.836
[THUNDER]

1489
01:19:05.409 --> 01:19:06.802
AH!

1490
01:19:06.845 --> 01:19:08.586
WAKE UP, WAKE UP.
IT'S RAINING.


1491
01:19:08.629 --> 01:19:09.805
COME ON, ALLIE,
DRINK.


1492
01:19:09.848 --> 01:19:12.068
OH! AHH! YES!

1493
01:19:21.381 --> 01:19:22.861
OH, NO.
NO.


1494
01:19:29.041 --> 01:19:31.348
IT'S TIME TO GO.

1495
01:19:32.436 --> 01:19:33.524
WHAT?

1496
01:19:34.699 --> 01:19:35.787
WHERE?

1497
01:19:37.833 --> 01:19:38.834
HOME.

1498
01:19:40.836 --> 01:19:42.925
TIME TO GO HOME.

1499
01:19:43.969 --> 01:19:47.712
COME HERE, ALLIE.
LIE WITH ME.


1500
01:19:47.755 --> 01:19:51.020
COME ON. SHH.

1501
01:19:52.325 --> 01:19:56.852
IT'S OK.
IT'S TIME TO GO.


1502
01:20:01.117 --> 01:20:03.554
ALLIE, CAN YOU
HEAR ME?


1503
01:20:03.597 --> 01:20:06.426
[HUMMING MELODY]

1504
01:20:10.953 --> 01:20:12.389
WHAT IS IT?

1505
01:20:14.521 --> 01:20:16.741
SHE'S SLIPPING AWAY.

1506
01:20:19.396 --> 01:20:24.401
[WHISPERING]
The Lord is my shepherd.
I shall not want...


1507
01:20:25.532 --> 01:20:27.621
I CAN'T TELL
WHAT SHE'S SAYING.


1508
01:20:30.755 --> 01:20:31.974
MAYBE SHE'S...

1509
01:20:32.017 --> 01:20:33.105
YEAH...

1510
01:20:35.368 --> 01:20:36.674
TALKING TO GOD.

1511
01:20:41.200 --> 01:20:45.726
OUR FATHER,
WHO ART IN HEAVEN,


1512
01:20:45.770 --> 01:20:47.598
HALLOWED BY THY NAME.

1513
01:20:47.641 --> 01:20:49.948
THY KINGDOM COME,
THY WILL BE DONE


1514
01:20:49.992 --> 01:20:52.908
ON EARTH AS IT IS
IN HEAVEN.


1515
01:20:52.951 --> 01:20:58.087
[SOBBING] GIVE US THIS DAY
OUR DAILY BREAD...


1516
01:21:24.287 --> 01:21:28.465
SHE WOULD'VE MADE IT
IF SHE HADN'T BEEN HURT.


1517
01:21:28.508 --> 01:21:31.555
SHE WAS STRONG.
SHE DIDN'T DESERVE
TO DIE THIS WAY.


1518
01:21:40.085 --> 01:21:41.957
I CAN'T BELIEVE
SHE'S GONE.


1519
01:21:44.524 --> 01:21:46.526
SHE HAD THIS
IN HER POCKET.


1520
01:21:53.577 --> 01:21:56.101
REST IN PEACE,
ALLIE.


1521
01:22:10.942 --> 01:22:14.380
[GRUNTING]

1522
01:22:19.168 --> 01:22:21.039
JASON, STOP.

1523
01:22:21.083 --> 01:22:24.216
NO, NO, LET GO.
IT'S NOT WHAT
YOU THINK.


1524
01:22:24.260 --> 01:22:28.003
SORRY. I THOUGHT YOU WERE
DRINKING SEA WATER.


1525
01:22:30.005 --> 01:22:31.963
I CAN'T STOP THROWING UP.

1526
01:22:32.007 --> 01:22:33.791
WELL, THAT'S...
THAT'S A GOOD SIGN.


1527
01:22:33.834 --> 01:22:35.532
YOUR BODY'S GETTING
RID OF THE TOXINS.


1528
01:22:35.575 --> 01:22:39.623
NO, NOT ANYMORE.
IT JUST DRY HEAVES NOW.


1529
01:22:39.666 --> 01:22:41.016
IT HURTS.

1530
01:22:42.930 --> 01:22:44.889
I'M SORRY, SUSAN.

1531
01:22:44.932 --> 01:22:46.195
SORRY? ABOUT WHAT?

1532
01:22:46.238 --> 01:22:49.328
I KNOW HOW MUCH
YOU HATE WEAKNESS.


1533
01:22:49.372 --> 01:22:52.810
I JUST HATE FEELING
LIKE MY LIFE IS
OUT OF CONTROL.


1534
01:22:52.853 --> 01:22:55.987
DOES THAT MAKE
ANY SENSE?


1535
01:22:57.206 --> 01:23:00.035
ABOUT AS MUCH SENSE
AS ANY OF THIS MAKES.


1536
01:23:05.431 --> 01:23:07.129
I'M SCARED, SUSAN.

1537
01:23:09.479 --> 01:23:12.395
I'M SCARED I'M GONNA DIE
ON THIS GODFORSAKEN RAFT.


1538
01:23:12.438 --> 01:23:15.876
STOP IT. DON'T
YOU DARE GIVE UP
ON ME, OK?


1539
01:23:15.920 --> 01:23:17.617
WE'RE GONNA LIVE
THROUGH THIS.


1540
01:23:17.661 --> 01:23:20.664
AND I'M TRYING.
I'M TRYING.


1541
01:23:20.707 --> 01:23:21.621
I'M JUST, YOU KNOW...

1542
01:23:21.665 --> 01:23:22.883
WELL, TRY HARDER.

1543
01:23:22.927 --> 01:23:24.189
IT HURTS SO BAD.

1544
01:23:24.233 --> 01:23:27.105
LOOK, WE'RE GONNA
MAKE IT, OK?


1545
01:23:32.067 --> 01:23:34.199
I NEED YOU
TO TRY HARDER.


1546
01:23:35.679 --> 01:23:36.767
REALLY?

1547
01:23:36.810 --> 01:23:39.161
YEAH, REALLY.

1548
01:24:11.889 --> 01:24:14.239
DID YOU HEAR SOMETHING?

1549
01:24:14.283 --> 01:24:16.111
[DISTANT ENGINE RUMBLING]

1550
01:24:43.007 --> 01:24:45.227
Susan: WHEN I FINALLY
SAW THE SHIP,


1551
01:24:45.270 --> 01:24:47.098
I THOUGHT IT WAS A MIRAGE.

1552
01:24:47.142 --> 01:24:50.449
I WAS JUST LOSING IT AGAIN.

1553
01:24:50.493 --> 01:24:53.191
THERE WAS NO WAY WE WERE
REALLY BEING RESCUED.


1554
01:24:53.235 --> 01:24:56.455
HEY! HEY! HEY!
HEY!


1555
01:24:56.499 --> 01:24:58.718
HA HA HA HA HA!

1556
01:24:58.762 --> 01:25:01.678
[HORN BLOWING]

1557
01:25:01.721 --> 01:25:04.855
AH, HA HA HA!

1558
01:25:04.898 --> 01:25:07.510
Susan:
THEN I HEARD JASON...


1559
01:25:07.553 --> 01:25:09.512
AND THE EXCITEMENT
IN HIS VOICE,


1560
01:25:09.555 --> 01:25:11.383
AND FIGURED
WE COULDN'T BOTH
BE DREAMING.


1561
01:25:11.427 --> 01:25:12.863
THEY FOUND
A RAFT.


1562
01:25:12.906 --> 01:25:14.081
OH, THANK GOD!

1563
01:25:14.125 --> 01:25:16.693
THEY STILL HAVE
TO GET THEM BOTH
ON BOARD.


1564
01:25:16.736 --> 01:25:18.477
BOTH? A MAN?
A WOMAN? WHO?


1565
01:25:18.521 --> 01:25:20.087
I DON'T KNOW
FOR SURE.


1566
01:25:20.131 --> 01:25:21.132
THEY'RE
ON BOARD.


1567
01:25:21.176 --> 01:25:22.699
WHO?

1568
01:25:22.742 --> 01:25:24.614
YOUNG MAN... AND
A YOUNG WOMAN.


1569
01:25:26.355 --> 01:25:29.314
JASON O'DONNELL...
AND SUSAN CLARKSON.


1570
01:25:29.358 --> 01:25:30.446
HA HA HA!

1571
01:25:30.489 --> 01:25:32.230
THANK YOU!
OH, THANK YOU,
THANK YOU!


1572
01:25:32.274 --> 01:25:33.797
THANK YOU
SO MUCH!


1573
01:26:33.944 --> 01:26:36.033
[CAR APPROACHING]

1574
01:26:37.774 --> 01:26:38.601
AH!

1575
01:26:41.778 --> 01:26:42.605
OH...

1576
01:26:52.223 --> 01:26:54.007
Susan:
IT WASN'T UNTIL LATER


1577
01:26:54.051 --> 01:26:56.009
THAT I REALIZED
WHAT MY MOM DID.


1578
01:26:56.053 --> 01:26:57.576
SUSANNAH.

1579
01:26:57.620 --> 01:27:01.145
SHE REFUSED TO GIVE UP,
AND SHE HELPED SAVE
OUR LIVES.


1580
01:27:03.060 --> 01:27:05.541
I GUESS, IN A WAY,
JASON AND MY MOM


1581
01:27:05.584 --> 01:27:08.674
WERE BOTH
TRYING TO TEACH ME
THE SAME THING...


1582
01:27:08.718 --> 01:27:12.330
THERE'S NOTHING WRONG
WITH NEEDING PEOPLE.


1583
01:27:12.374 --> 01:27:16.769
THAT'S WHAT MAKES US STRONG,
THAT'S WHAT MAKES US HUMAN,


1584
01:27:16.813 --> 01:27:18.771
AND THAT'S WHY
I'M ALIVE TODAY.